With Acumatica ERP, your company can easily configure and adjust sales order processing, accurately fulfill sales orders, process shipments and transfers of items, bill customers for sales orders, record customer returns, and perform other tasks required by the sales workflow of your company. Acumatica ERP provides flexible configuration options so that you can configure the system to fit the requirements of your company and efficiently manage business processes. In this topic, you will read about the sales order-related processes that you can configure and perform in the Sales Orders module.{br}{TOC} ==Configuring Order Workflows== Acumatica ERP includes a set of predefined order types for common distribution operations. To adjust the system to your needs and maintain your business processes, you can specify specific settings for each predefined order type. For an order type, you can specify posting settings and numbering sequences, specify whether the orders of this type and related documents should be on hold when they are entered or when the customer&rsquo;s credit limit has been exceeded, set up parallel or multistage approval, and specify other settings specific to order type. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__CNF_OrderTypes|Predefined Sales Order Types].{br}
You can define custom order types based on the predefined order types to meet specific order processing requirements. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Custom_Order_Types|Custom Sales Order Types]. Also, users can simplify multi-step processing and configure quick processing for a particular order type (predefined or custom) so that users can process the orders of this type with just one click. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Quick_Process_Workflow|Quick Processing of Sales Orders]. ==Shipping Orders Fully or in Parts== You can specify flexible shipping options for a sales order. The shipping rules specified for a particular sales order define whether the goods for the sales order should be shipped only in full or partial shipments for the available quantities are allowed. For each customer, you can specify the shipping rule to be used by default for the orders to this customer. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Default_Shipping_Rules|Shipping Rule Settings]. ==Integrating Acumatica ERP with Local and National Carriers and Calculating Freight Charges== You can configure local carriers to be used for shipping the orders, or integrate your system with nationwide carriers, such as FedEx or UPS. For local carriers, the system can estimate shipping costs by using the carriers&rsquo; predefined rates. For details on freight calculation for orders shipped via local carriers and via nationwide carriers, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\CS__con_Freight_Calculation|Freight Calculation]. {br}
With the ''Shipping Carrier Integration'' feature enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, users can get real-time shipping rates on sales orders from the nationwide carriers, and select the lowest freight cost for customers by comparing carrier rates on the fly. The customers can track their own order and check the delivery status of each box by using tracking numbers, which are provided through integration. Shipping terms configured in the system allow insurance and handling fees for labor and packaging fees to be added seamlessly. For details, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\CS__con_Integration_with_Carriers|Integration with Carriers]. ==Configuring Auto-Packaging for Shipped Items== With Acumatica ERP you can make processing of shipments more effective by configuring automatic packaging suggestions both for orders shipped via integrated carriers and via local carriers. With the ''Automated Packaging'' feature enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form, the system automatically selects the minimum set of packaging boxes for each sales order to be shipped, depending on the weight and volume of the ordered items. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_WeightVolume|Weight and Volume in Sales Orders]. ==Using Sales Prices in Orders and Applying Discounts== The prices and discounts that are maintained in the Accounts Receivable module are used in the sales orders and invoices. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Prices_SO|Sales Prices in Sales Documents] and [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Discounts_SO|Discount Application in Sales Documents]. ==Calculating Taxes for Sales Orders== The rate and the amount of sales tax that apply to ordered items depend on many factors, including the types of items purchased, the delivery address of the customer, the address of the selling branch, and your organization&rsquo;s business presence (if it has one) in the state of the customer. With Acumatica ERP, you can set up the taxes to be automatically applied to Sales Orders documents. For details, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Sales_Taxes_on_Sales_Orders|Tax Application in Sales Documents]. ==Tracking Sales Proposals== To record planned sales, you can create quotes that then can be used as a base for preparing a sales order, invoice order, or cash sale order. For more information on processing quotes, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_scn_Sale_Quote|Processing Pre-Sale Quotes]. ==Processing Sales of Stock and Non-Stock Items== Multiple order types that are predefined in Acumatica ERP support various business processes. Through sales orders of different types, you can process sales of inventory items (stock and non-stock) for credit and for cash, sales with transfer of items between warehouses, orders with both stock and non-stock items, and other orders that involve inventory items. For detailed descriptions of these processes, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Inventory_Sales|Processing Sales of Stock Items] and [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_NStock_Sales|Processing Sales of Non-Stock Items]. ==Reviewing Item Availability Information and Allocating Stock Items== During order entry, you can access item availability information to check whether a sufficient quantity of the needed items is available for sale. Also, for a particular sales order, you can perform stock reservations (and specify items&rsquo; lot or serial numbers, if required) so that the items promised to a customer cannot be shipped to another customer. When items are stocked at multiple warehouses, this helps avoid overstocks and stockouts because the system gives you the ability to reserve items at any warehouse and automates transfers. ==Attaching Files and Notes == You can attach to a sales order scanned images or electronic versions of customer orders to facilitate tracking and processing of the order. You can also add notes with shipping and handling instructions to sales orders or specific lines of sales orders, and configure any order type so that the system will copy attached notes and files from sales orders of this type to related shipments and invoices. ==Printing Documents and Labels== If you need printed copies of the documents in the Sales Orders module, you can print any sales order or quote, shipment pick list, shipment confirmation, or invoice. Also, if an integrated carrier is used for shipping items, you can configure the printing of carrier labels. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Printing_Docs|Printing Sales Documents] and [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Carriers_Label|Carrier Labels and Tracking Numbers]. ==Shipping Orders in Full and Partially== You can specify a different delivery date for each line item on a sales order, and prepare separate shipments for particular items. Also, you can prepare a partial shipment depending on the inventory availability information of the item. In these cases, the system splits a sales order into multiple shipments from different warehouses For more details, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Partial_Shipments|Partial Shipping of Orders]. ==Processing Orders for Items That Are Out of Stock== Acumatica ERP supports multiple scenarios for tracking and processing orders that have been prepared when there are insufficient item quantities:[anchor|#_d8763532-01d8-42c4-b56d-504be422d7d5] *Transfer order preparation for a sales order: You can allocate the insufficient item quantity in other warehouse, and then prepare a transfer order to transfer the items to the destination warehouse. Once the items are received, the sales order can be processed further. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__MNG_TR_Orders|Sale with Transferred Stock Items]. *Sales order for drop-shipping: If the ''Drop Shipments'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, you can mark a sales order line as intended for drop-shipping; when you process the sales order further, the customer receives the goods directly from one of your vendors. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_scn_DropShip|Processing Sales for Drop-Shipment]. *Back ordering: If back ordering is allowed for a sales order, you can ship the items partially; the system tracks the remaining quantities in an order after partial shipment and places a partially shipped order to back order. Once the remaining item quantity becomes available in inventory, back-orders can be replanned and processed further. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_ReplanBackOrders|Back Ordering and Replanning Back Orders]. *Purchase for sale: If the ''Sales Order to Purchase Order Link'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form, you can mark a sales orders line that is out of stock fully or partially, so that the remaining quantity will be purchased directly for this order. For more information on how to use the goods received from vendors for fulfilling specific sales orders, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Purchase_for_Sale|Processing Purchased Items for Sale].
==Processing Customer Returns== Acumatica ERP provides the flexibility to manage various types of customer returns. Your company can set up its own return policies by using specific predefined order types and by creating custom order types for authorized and unauthorized returns. You can perform authorized and unauthorized returns, returns for credit and for cash, and returns with replacement, for the same price or for a changed price. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Sale_Return|Processing Customer Returns]. ==Processing Sales Through Point of Sale == If the ''Advanced SO Invoices'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, a user can add stock items directly to a Sales Orders invoice without creating and processing the associated sales order and shipment. This sales workflow is used for simplified processing of direct sales with the integration of an external point of sale system. ==Reserving Payments for Sales Orders== If your company requires prepayments or payments to be made for particular orders, you can create payments and prepayments and reserve them for specific orders, and then track how payment amounts have been applied to one invoice or multiple invoices prepared for the order. ==Converting Opportunities to Sales Orders Documents== With Acumatica ERP, salespeople can convert customer relationship management (CRM) opportunities to sales orders without re-entering pricing and discount information. Customer service personnel can easily locate customer orders to verify their delivery status. Order fulfillment personnel can associate tasks and activities with each order. For more information, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CR__MNG_Opportunities|Managing Opportunities]. ==Mass-Processing of Documents== To simplify regular operations that are performed, Acumatica ERP provides mass-processing forms on which you can perform the commonly used operations for multiple orders, shipments, or invoices at a time. You can also schedule any of the operations to be performed automatically at a convenient interval (daily or weekly).

To maintain data consistency during the sales operations, the Sales Orders module is tightly integrated with other system modules. The Sales Orders module does not produce General Ledger transactions directly; during the order fulfillment processes, these transactions are generated from the Inventory and Accounts Receivable modules. Together these modules provide integrated order fulfillment, inventory management, and financial accounting. The following diagram illustrates the documents that are produced in the Sales Orders module and the related documents processed in other modules.[anchor|#_d5ebc332-fab4-4f17-be1f-5ac758636629][anchor|#_3acd5c41-9832-4977-a0aa-c1edefbf8d38][image:UserGuide/Images/SO_Connection_Overview.png|popup|450px]
The Sales Orders process typically starts when a user enters a sales order document. Acumatica ERP provides multiple predefined order types that support typical business operations; you select the order type depending on which process you need to perform.{br}

When you enter an order, in each order line, you can select a particular stock or non-stock item from the list of configured inventory items. The Sales Orders module provides instant access to accurate inventory allocation information. For the stock items, the system checks the item availability information and notifies the user if the item quantity specified in a sales order line is currently not available. {br}

If a sales order requires the shipping of items during processing, the related shipment document has to be prepared and confirmed. After the shipment of items is completed (or if the sales order does not require shipping), the Sales Orders (SO) invoice document has to be prepared for the sales order. On release of this SO invoice, the related Accounts Receivable document (invoice or cash sale) becomes available in the Accounts Receivable module; this document should be then paid by the customer for the shipped goods. {br}

To keep the inventory information up to date, the system generates the inventory transactions from the Sales Orders module when a user processes a sales order. When the sold goods are issued from the inventory, an inventory issue is generated to update the item availability information in the Inventory module. When a return of items is processed through a sales order, an inventory receipt is generated to reflect the receipt of the returned item to inventory. When a transfer of items is processed through transfer order, an inventory transfer is generated to reflect the item movement between locations or warehouses.{br}

The Sales Orders module provides flexible pricing and discounting policies by using the sales prices and discounts that are maintained in the Accounts Receivable module. {br}

For financial accounting processes, the Inventory module and the Accounts Receivable module are integrated with the General Ledger module. When you release an inventory transaction and an Accounts Receivable document, the batches of the corresponding transactions are generated in the General Ledger module. 
==Related Articles==
*[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__SO_Features|Sales Orders Processes]

For the shipment of goods, your business may use local carriers as well as carriers that provide nationwide services. When you configure local carriers, you specify their estimated predefined rates. {br}

Large carriers operating over a broad geographical area—such as FedEx, USPS, and UPS—provide shipping solutions to clients with whom they have service agreements. A user can access the carrier&rsquo;s system, enter package details, get actual rates, print authorized labels for shipments, and track the delivery of shipments. If you configure integration with the carrier, your users don&rsquo;t need to enter the same information into both Acumatica ERP and the carrier&rsquo;s system.{br}

In Acumatica ERP, you can configure integration with FedEx, USPS and UPS; we refer to these carriers as ''integrated carriers''. The functionality of integrating with carriers is available only if the ''Shipping Carrier Integration'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form.((({S:Warn}The integration of Acumatica ERP with the carriers (such as UPS, or FedEx) does not support international shipments.
))){br}{TOC}
==Carrier-Specific Plug-ins and Their Parameters==
The FedEx, UPS, and USPS carriers provide application programming interfaces (APIs) that allow their systems to be integrated with their clients&rsquo; systems. Acumatica ERP provides the following plug-ins for integration with these carriers: [anchor|#ul_ull_zjy_ls]
*{{PX.UpsCarrier.UpsCarrier}}: For use with UPS
*{{PX.FedExCarrier.FedExCarrier}}: For use with FedEx
*{{PX.StampsCarrier.StampsCarrier}}: For use with USPS
((({S:Hint}Plug-ins for other carriers can be developed on request.
)))
Before you configure integration with a carrier, your company should have an account with the carrier and a signed service agreement. For each of the plug-ins, you specify parameters that are specific to the carrier, including the account number and password for authorization with the carrier&rsquo;s system. Such services as ''FedEx SmartPost'' and ''UPS SurePost'' require additional service contracts to be signed with the respective carriers. These services employ the USPS for final delivery of low-weight packages to customers in the residential areas.{br}

To configure integration with a carrier, you use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_20_77_00|Carriers] ([~/?ScreenId=CS207700|CS207700]) form. On the this form, you specify a name to be used for this carrier in your system, select the appropriate plug-in, and enter the values for the parameters, which are specific to the plug-in you have selected. Some parameters are used for authentication with the carrier's system, while others are used to print carrier labels. All plug-ins include a parameter that can be used if recipient's signature is required to confirm shipments.{br}

Also, you can set up notification of the recipients about shipments sent via the carrier. For the '''NOTIFY''' (Send Notification to Recipient) parameter that each of the plug-ins has, you select the check box to set up this notification. Then on release of each shipment, the carrier&rsquo;s online service will generate a notification email for the email address of the contact specified for the shipment on the '''Shipping Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302000|SO302000]) form.{br}

For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__How_Integrate_FedEx|To Set Up Integration with FedEx], and [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__How_Integrate_UPS|To Set Up Integration with UPS].
== Ship via Codes Based on Carrier Service Methods==
Generally, carriers provide multiple service methods. Each service method has its own rates and time frame for delivery. In Acumatica ERP, for each service method of the integrated carrier to be used by your company, you can define a ship via code by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_20_75_00|Ship via Codes] ([~/?ScreenId=CS207500|CS207500]) form. Then, when a user creates a sales order, the user can easily select the appropriate carrier and its service method by specifying the appropriate ship via code.{br}

You also can specify for each ship via code whether shipment confirmation for each box is required and whether at least one package (box) is required to confirm a shipment. For details, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__How_Create_Ship_Via_Codes|To Create Ship via Codes for the Integrated Carrier].
==Use of Customer Accounts with Carriers==
You can set up billing of the customers, rather than your company, for shipping if the customers provide information about their accounts with the carrier. On the '''Customer Accounts''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_20_77_00|Carriers] ([~/?ScreenId=CS207700|CS207700]) form, create a list of customers with their locations and their accounts with the integrated carrier. Only customers with the '''Active''' check box selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_30_00|Customers] ([~/?ScreenId=AR303000|AR303000]) form can be billed by the carrier. For each customer, you can view the list of customer accounts with carriers on the '''Delivery Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_30_00|Customers] form.
==Automatic Packaging ==
For effective integration with carriers, you can configure the system to automatically suggest packaging options for sales orders and then for shipments based on item quantities, weights, or volumes. To use this functionality, you need to enable the ''Automatic Packaging'' feature on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form.{br}

For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Automated_Shipments|Automatic Packaging for Integrated Carriers].
==Freight Calculation==
Once integration with carriers is configured, the system will be able to automatically evaluate freight cost on shipping the sales orders via integrated carriers. On the '''Shipping Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, for each sales order, you can click the '''Shop for Rates''' button to view the freight costs for the specified packages if sent by different methods of the selected carrier available for this particular shipment. You can then select the most appropriate ship via code for this shipment. The full freight amount you charge your customers may include not only the freight your organization is charged by carriers (freight cost), but also insurance, handling, packaging, and premium freight amounts defined by your shipping terms. You can view the freight total on the '''Totals''' tab.{br}

For details on defining and calculating freight, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\CS__con_Freight_Calculation|Freight Calculation].
