Acumatica ERP provides predefined order types for common order processing operations. When you create a new order on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, you select the appropriate predefined type, which defines the information to be entered, the processing operations to be performed for order completion. and the documents to be generated during the order processing.((({S:Hint} To be able to create an order of a particular type, you first need to activate this order type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form. ))) This chapter describes the settings of the preconfigured types of orders that you can use for performing basic order management, sales, and return operations. ==In This Chapter==[anchor|#table_hjd_ydl_ldb] {| class="checklist invisiblechecklist" | width="100%" |- | [anchor|#ul_ijd_ydl_ldb] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__CNF_OrderType_CM|CM Order Type (Credit Memo)] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__CNF_OrderType_CR|CR Order Type (Cash Return)] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__CNF_OrderType_CS|CS Order Type (Cash Sale)] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__CNF_OrderType_IN|IN Order Type (Invoice)] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__CNF_OrderType_QT|QT Order Type (Quote)] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__CNF_OrderType_RC|RC Order Type (Return for Credit)]
