If the goods are being shipped by an integrated carrier, the tax category is applied to only the amount of freight that exceeds the freight cost. The list of taxes applied to the specified amount consists of the taxes from both the tax category and the tax zone of the customer&rsquo;s delivery address (the specified tax zone of the customer location or, if one has not been specified, the tax zone automatically determined by the ZIP code of the delivery address). ==Sales Taxes on Sales Orders Invoices== When a sales order is shipped, the system generates an SO invoice, which you can view on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. For these invoices, the system copies all the details from the associated sales orders. Sales orders with different tax zones cannot be added to the same invoice. When you mass-create invoices for multiple sales orders by using the ''Prepare Invoice'' action on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_10_00|Process Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO501000|SO501000]) form, the system groups the sales orders by tax zone.((({S:Hint}When a user mass-prepares invoices to a customer that is assigned to the tax zone configured for Avalara, shipments that have different ship-to addresses can be consolidated into one SO invoice. ))) Also, you can manually create invoices to bill customers for services rendered, or you can enter cash sales when the customer immediately pays for the services. You can create an invoice by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_10_00|Invoices and Memos] ([~/?ScreenId=AR301000|AR301000]) or the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. Cash sales can be created on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_40_00|Cash Sales] ([~/?ScreenId=AR304000|AR304000]) form. {br}
The system inserts the default tax zone for the accounts receivable or SO invoice or cash sale (displayed in the '''Customer Tax Zone''' box on the '''Financial Details''' tab of the applicable form), copying it as follows:[anchor|#ol_npz_xch_2l] #From the tax zone specified for the opportunity on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_40_00|Opportunities] ([~/?ScreenId=CR304000|CR304000]) form if the order has been created from an opportunity that has a tax zone specified. #From the tax zone of the customer location specified on the document. Tax zones for customer locations can be selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_30_20|Customer Locations] ([~/?ScreenId=AR303020|AR303020]) form. #From the tax zone associated with the selling branch if no tax zone is specified for this customer location. If the ''Branch Accounting'' feature is not activated on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, the tax zone assigned to your organization on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_20_00|Branches] ([~/?ScreenId=CS102000|CS102000]) form is used.
