Transfer orders are generated automatically from the transfer requests when the stock for sales order fulfillment is reserved in remote warehouses, or created manually to account for goods that are moved from one warehouse to another without a sale. Also, transfer orders can be generated in the process of replenishment, to move goods from the source warehouse to the warehouse where they are needed for sale. This part of the guide describes how to prepare transfer orders for sales order fulfillment, and how to apply landed costs to transfer orders in Acumatica ERP.. ==In This Part==[anchor|#_3dc32057-3ccf-49f7-91d0-fd69ec3c55eb] {| class="checklist invisiblechecklist" | width="100%" |- | [anchor|#_ce5d05fc-8a7a-4d4d-b122-c59e3ae1fba8] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_scn_Sale_with_Transfer|Processing Steps for a Sale with Transfer] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Transfer_Variations|Variations in the Transfer Order Process]
