When you process a sale of inventory items, you can reserve one line or multiple lines of an open sales order of the ''SO'' or ''SA'' type in a warehouse other than the warehouse selected in the line. To be able to process a sales order with stock items that are reserved in a remote warehouse (that is, a warehouse other than the one specified in the order), you first need to transfer the reserved items from the remote source warehouse (at which the items were reserved) to the destination warehouse (for which the sales order is processed). For this purpose, a transfer order of the ''TR'' predefined order type is prepared and processed.((({S:Hint} For a description of other scenarios that may require preparing and processing transfer orders, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Transfer_Variations|Variations in the Transfer Order Process], ))) The processing of a sale with the transfer of items involves the actions and generated documents shown in the following diagram.[anchor|#fig_xqs_s4n_jdb][anchor|#image_sqs_xrk_3db][image:UserGuide/Images/Inventory_Sale_With_Transferring_Stock.png|popup|400px]{br}{TOC} ==1. Enter the Sales Order== You create a new sales order of the ''SO'' type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. If the order is created with the ''On Hold'' status, you should clear the '''Hold''' check box for the order to process it further. For more details on which information is to be specified in an order, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_SO_OrderInfo|Sales Order Entry]. ==2. Reserve Items in the Source Warehouse== To obtain the sufficient quantity of items for the sales order, you manually reserve the quantity for each specific item in the source warehouse. To be able to complete the sales order, you first need to perform a transfer of items allocated in a warehouse other than the destination warehouse. For the items allocated in a warehouse other than the warehouse specified in the sales order, the system automatically generates transfer requests of the ''SO Allocated'' plan type. Based on the transfer requests, you prepare transfer orders for these items. ==3. Prepare the Transfer Order== To create a transfer order (an order of the ''TR'' type) for a sales order, you click '''Actions &gt; Create Transfer Order''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. {br}
On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_90_00|Create Transfer Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO509000|SO509000]) form, which opens, you can create one transfer order or multiple transfer orders for transfer requests with the ''SO Allocated'' plan type. You can select the transfer requests by source and destination warehouses, item class, and product workgroup. After reviewing the resulting list, you can generate transfer orders for each line in the list, or you can select the orders to be generated by selecting the check boxes to the left of the plan types. ==4. Prepare the Shipment== A transfer order is fulfilled by one shipment or by multiple shipments from the source warehouse (in which the item is allocated) to the destination warehouse. You can create a shipment for a transfer order from the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Create Shipment''' on the form toolbar. If you need to create shipments for multiple transfer orders, you can run the ''Create Shipment'' process by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_10_00|Process Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO501000|SO501000]) form. The shipments will be grouped by source and destination warehouses and by stock items. The item quantities on the shipment are deducted from the '''Available''' and '''Available for Shipping''' quantities and added to the '''SO Allocated''' quantity; you can see these quantities on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_40_20_00|Inventory Allocation Details] ([~/?ScreenId=IN402000|IN402000]) form, as well as on other forms.{br}
You can print a pick list for each shipment by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Print Pick List'''on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302000|SO302000]) form. Alternatively, you can print pick lists for multiple shipments by applying the ''Print Pick Lists'' action for the selected shipments on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_30_00|Process Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO503000|SO503000]) form. ==5. Confirm the Shipment== You can confirm each shipment by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302000|SO302000]) form. Upon shipment confirmation, the quantities of items on the shipment are added to the SO Shipped quantity. ==6. Update Inventory== To promptly update the item quantities in the destination warehouse, you click '''Actions''' > '''Update IN''' on the form toolbar; once you do, the system generates the inventory transfer document that issue items from the source warehouse. The item quantity is deducted from SO Shipped and added to In Transit. (These quantities are displayed on a variety of Inventory inquiries and reports.) ==7. Release the Inventory Transfer== To release the inventory transfer, you click '''Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_40_00|Transfers] ([~/?ScreenId=IN304000|IN304000]) form. On release of the inventory transfer, a batch of General Ledger transactions is generated that moves the cost of transferred items to the In-Transit account. ==8. Prepare the Transfer Receipt== To complete the two-step inventory transfer, you should prepare the transfer receipt (that is, a receipt of the ''Transfer Receipt'' type) of items to the destination warehouse. You create a transfer receipt on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form and add to the receipt the lines from one transfer order or multiple transfer orders. A transfer receipt may include only some of the lines from a transfer order; you can also change the quantity in a particular line if the items specified in this line were received partially. ==9. Release the Transfer Receipt== You release the transfer receipt by clicking '''Release''' on the table toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form. On release of the transfer receipt, the inventory receipt document is generated to receive the items to the destination warehouse. ==10. Release the Inventory Receipt== You release the inventory receipt by clicking '''Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_10_00|Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=IN301000|IN301000]) form. On release of the inventory transfer, a batch of General Ledger transactions is generated that moves the cost of transferred items from the In-Transit account. Thus, the quantity of the item that has been transferred from the source warehouse to the destination warehouse becomes available for sale. The item quantity is deducted from the In-Transit quantity and added to Quantity Available and Quantity on Hand.{br}
After the transferred stock item or items have been received to the destination warehouse, you can complete the sales order in the same way as if you have just entered it. (For the general steps of sales order processing, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_scn_Sale_with_Shipping|Sale of Stock Items with Shipping].) ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__MNG_Landed_Costs|Allocating Landed Costs]

Transfer orders can be created manually to account for goods that are moved from one warehouse to another, or generated automatically when the stock for sales order fulfillment is reserved in a warehouse (or multiple warehouses) other than the one specified in the sales order. Also, transfer orders can be generated in the process of replenishment, to move goods from the source warehouse to the warehouse where they are needed for sale. For a detailed description of a general workflow of a sale with items that are reserved in a remote warehouse, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_scn_Sale_with_Transfer|Processing Steps for a Sale with Transfer].{br}
In addition to the general workflow, the following scenarios are available for transfer orders:[anchor|#ul_q2v_2jq_3db] *You can use transfer orders for transferring items between warehouses without a sale being associated with the transfer. For this purpose, you can create an individual transfer order of the ''TR'' type by entering all the required information on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. The general process is the same as described in the [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_scn_Sale_with_Transfer|Processing Steps for a Sale with Transfer] topic, starting from Step 3. If needed, you can reserve stock in the source warehouse for each line item on the transfer order by selecting the line and clicking the '''Allocations''' button on the table toolbar, and then creating additional allocation schedules. *You can create transfer orders for replenishment requests by transfer on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_90_00|Create Transfer Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO509000|SO509000]) form. For more information about inventory replenishment, see [HelpRoot_InvMgmt\IN__MNG_Replenishment|Replenishing Inventory Items].
==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__How_Create_Transfer_Order|To Create a Transfer Order (TR)] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__How_Process_Multiple_TRs|To Create Shipments for Multiple Orders] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__MNG_Landed_Costs|Allocating Landed Costs]

If you need to record the movement of goods from one warehouse to another, you create a transfer order of the predefined ''TR'' type. You can mass-create transfer orders for multiple sales orders simultaneously on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_90_00|Create Transfer Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO509000|SO509000]) form. ==To Create Transfer Orders for Multiple Orders==[anchor|#_ae58b246-d6b9-42c0-9a5c-c4075e477dd7] #Open the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_90_00|Create Transfer Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO509000|SO509000]) form by searching for or navigating to it. #:((({S:Hint}To open any form, you can navigate to it or search for it (by its name or by its form ID without periods). For more information about search capabilities, see [HelpRoot_Interface\UIG__con_New_UI_Search|Search in the Modern UI]. ))) #In the '''Creation Date''' box, select the date on which the transfer order or orders should be prepared. #In the table, select the unlabeled check boxes next to the needed line or lines with the ''SO Allocated'' plan type. #Click '''Process''' on the form toolbar, or click '''Process All''' to process all lines shown in the table.
==Notes About the Procedure==[anchor|#_ac36deee-0938-4187-bef3-37aff75b49c5] The notes in this section describe the nuances of the UI elements available on the form, such as when an element is required and when it is not, and when the system fills in settings by default. This section can include other notes.{br}
Note the following about this procedure:[anchor|#ul_fqz_wsz_jz] *After you have created shipments, you need to confirm each shipment and create transfer receipts for transfer orders, if any have been processed. *To narrow the range of documents shown in the table, do any of the following: **In the '''From Warehouse''' and '''To Warehouse''' boxes, specify the source and destination warehouses, respectively. **In the '''Customer''' box, specify a particular customer whose orders you want to process. **In the '''Item Class ID''', specify a particular item class. **In the '''Inventory ID''' box, specify a particular inventory item to see the transfer requests for this item. **Specify and apply a filter to select documents by specific criteria. You can create a reusable filter for the form that, once created, gives you the ability to display particular documents each time you bring up this form. For more information, see [HelpRoot_Interface\IB_Filters|Filters].

To process a sale of items directly to the customer and when you are receiving payment at that time (by cash, check, or credit card), you can create a cash sale order of the ''CS'' order type by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. The processing of cash sales orders involves the actions and generated documents shown in the following diagram.((({S:Hint}If quick processing is configured for the ''CS'' order type, you can perform complete processing of the order directly from the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Quick_Process_Workflow|Quick Processing of Sales Orders]. )))[anchor|#fig_dc5_dmr_gdb][anchor|#image_ec5_dmr_gdb][image:UserGuide/Images/Inventory_Sale_By_Cash.png|popup|300px] The following sections describe in detail the processing steps shown in the diagram.{br}{TOC} ==1. Enter the Sales Order== A new sales order of the ''CS'' type is created on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. You can save the order of the ''CS'' type only after you specify the payment information, including the payment method, cash account, and payment reference number (and the card information if the payment is performed with a credit card). {br}
The reference number for a new order is generated according to the numbering sequence assigned to this order type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form. If the order is created with the ''On Hold'' status, you should clear the '''Hold''' check box for the order to process it further. ==2. Prepare the Sales Orders Invoice== You can prepare the Sales Orders (SO) invoice by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Prepare Invoice''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, or you can create invoices by specifying the ''Prepare Invoice'' action on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_10_00|Process Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO501000|SO501000]) form and processing multiple selected orders. For the cash sale order, an SO invoice of the ''Cash Sale'' type is prepared. {br}
Any prepared SO invoice can be reviewed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. You can print an SO invoice by clicking '''Reports &gt; Print Invoice''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] form. ==3. Release the Sales Orders Invoice== To release the Sales Orders invoice, you click '''Actions &gt; Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] form. When the SO invoice of the ''Cash Sale'' type is released, a batch of General Ledger transactions is generated. Also, when the SO invoice is released, the system automatically generates a corresponding inventory issue with the date and posting period of the SO invoice. The related Accounts Receivable cash sale with the same reference number becomes available for reviewing on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_40_00|Cash Sales] ([~/?ScreenId=AR304000|AR304000]) form. For more information on processing Accounts Receivable cash sales, see [HelpRoot_Financials\AR__MNG_ProcessingARDocs|Processing AR Documents]. ==4. Release the Inventory Issue== The generated inventory issue is released automatically if the '''Automatically Release IN Documents''' check box is selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_10_10_00|Sales Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SO101000|SO101000]) form. If this check box is cleared, you have to release the inventory issue manually by clicking '''Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_20_00|Issues] ([~/?ScreenId=IN302000|IN302000]) form. On release of the inventory issue, a batch of General Ledger transactions is generated. ==Important Notes== Note the following about the processing of cash sales orders:[anchor|#_7ae8fe89-5d47-4673-aa43-53ab950f4ce8] *If you process a cash sales order with only non-stock items, no inventory issue is generated when the SO invoice of the ''Cash Sale'' type is released. *For non-stock items and services, you can enter a process a cash sale directly on the[HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_40_00|Cash Sales] ([~/?ScreenId=AR304000|AR304000]) form without creating and processing a cash sale order. *For items that have lot or serial numbers tracked in Acumatica ERP, you can specify these numbers, thus indicating that these particular items have been delivered to the customer.
==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__CNF_OrderType_CS|CS Order Type (Cash Sale)]

Non-stock items in Acumatica ERP are used for representing the products that cannot be stocked in warehouses (such as services or charges) or the physical entities whose quantities you do not need to track. Sales of non-stock items can be processed either through an accounts receivable invoice from the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_10_00|Invoices and Memos] ([~/?ScreenId=AR301000|AR301000]) form or through a sales order from the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. Depending on the business requirements of the company, you may want to streamline sales processing and enter all sales, including the sale of non-stock items, through sales orders.{br}
The topics of this chapter describe the sales processes that can be performed for non-stock items. ==In This Chapter==[anchor|#_e18eff61-c021-4af0-8830-1ead13e8aa96] {| class="checklist invisiblechecklist" | width="100%" |- | [anchor|#ul_jyv_bv2_1x] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_scn_Service_Sale|Sale of Services] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Sale_NonStock|Sale of Non-Stock Items with Shipping]
|}

In Acumatica ERP, services are represented by non-stock items that have the '''Require Shipment''' check box cleared in the item&rsquo;s settings on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202000|IN202000]) form. If a sales order includes only services that do not require shipment, the typical processing of the sales order involves the steps and generated documents shown in the following diagram.[anchor|#fig_rdm_bwr_gdb][anchor|#image_sdm_bwr_gdb][image:UserGuide/Images/Sale_of_Services.png|popup|450px]
The following sections describe in detail the processing steps shown in the diagram.{br}{TOC}
==1. Enter the Sales Order==
You create the sales order of the ''SO'' or ''IN'' type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. Reference numbers for new orders are generated according to the numbering sequence assigned to this order type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form. For the sales order, on the '''Document Details''' tab, you add lines with items to be sold. Non-stock items are considered to be always available and cannot be allocated. If the order has been created with the ''On Hold'' status, you should clear the '''On Hold''' check box for the order to process it further.{br}

On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] form, you can print a sales order by clicking '''Reports &gt; Print Sales Order/Quote''' on the form toolbar. 
==2. Prepare the Sales Orders Invoice==
You can prepare a Sales Orders invoice for a particular order you are viewing on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Prepare Invoice''' on the form toolbar. Alternatively, you can create multiple invoices by selecting the ''Prepare Invoice'' action and processing multiple orders (either all orders or only those you select) on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_10_00|Process Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO501000|SO501000]) form. {br}

Any prepared Sales Orders invoice can be reviewed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. You can print the Sales Orders invoice on this form by clicking '''Reports &gt; Print Invoice''' on the form toolbar. 
==3. Release the Sales Orders Invoice==
To release the Sales Orders invoice, you click '''Actions &gt; Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. When the Sales Orders invoice is released, a batch of General Ledger transactions is generated. Also, when this invoice is released, the related Accounts Receivable invoice with the same reference number becomes available on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_10_00|Invoices and Memos] ([~/?ScreenId=AR301000|AR301000]) form. For more information on the further processing of Accounts Receivable invoices, see [HelpRoot_Financials\AR__MNG_InvoicesMemos|Processing Invoices].{br}

No inventory issue is generated because non-stock items are not tracked in inventory. ((({S:Hint}If you have prepared a sales order with mixed lines of items (stock or non-stock, or both) that require shipping and non-stock items that do not require shipping, the shipment prepared for the order includes only the items that require shipping, while the prepared Sales Orders invoice for the sales order lists all the items from the order. The inventory issue generated on release of the Sales Orders invoice includes only stock items because their quantities are tracked in inventory. 
)))
