Although non-stock items are not tracked in inventory, you may want to process them through shipment, so that these items will be listed in pick lists and shipment confirmations, if the customer has requested the listing of these items in these documents. If a non-stock item has the '''Require Shipment''' check box selected in the item&rsquo;s settings on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202000|IN202000]) form, the item is processed through shipments. {br}

If a sales order includes only non-stock items requiring shipment, the processing of the sales order involves the steps and generated documents shown in the following diagram.[anchor|#fig_gxr_bpd_h5][anchor|#image_y1h_nr5_dt][image:UserGuide/Images/Sale_of_Non_Stock_With_Shipping.png|popup|400px]
The following sections describe in detail the processing steps shown in the diagram.{br}{TOC}
==1. Enter the Sales Order==
You create a new sales order of the ''SO'' type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. Reference numbers for new orders are generated in accordance with the numbering sequence assigned to this order type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form. On the '''Document Details''' tab, you add lines with the items to be sold. Non-stock items are considered to be always available; thus, they cannot be allocated.{br}

New orders of the ''SO'' type are saved with the ''On Hold'' status by default if the '''Hold Documents on Entry''' check box is selected for this order type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] form. You should clear the '''Hold''' check box on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] form for the order to process the order further. {br}

On this form, you can print a sales order by clicking '''Reports &gt; Print Sales Order/Quote''' on the form toolbar. 
==2. Prepare the Shipment==
You can create a shipment for an individual sales order you are viewing on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Create Shipment''' on the form toolbar. Alternatively, you can create shipments for multiple orders on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_10_00|Process Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO501000|SO501000]) form by selecting the ''Create Shipment'' action and processing multiple orders (either all orders or only those you select). The newly created shipments will have the ''Open'' status if the '''Hold Shipments on Entry''' check box is cleared on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_10_10_00|Sales Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SO101000|SO101000]) form and the ''On Hold'' status if this check box is selected.{br}

Any prepared shipment can be reviewed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302000|SO302000]) form. On this form, you can print a pick list for a particular shipment. For multiple shipments with the ''On Hold'' and ''Open'' statuses, you can print pick lists by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_30_00|Process Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO503000|SO503000]) form. For more details, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Shipment_Processing|Shipment Processing Steps].
==3. Confirm the Shipment==
You can confirm a shipment that you are viewing on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302000|SO302000]) form by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Confirm Shipment''' on the form toolbar. Alternatively, you can confirm multiple shipments on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_30_00|Process Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO503000|SO503000]) form by selecting the ''Confirm Shipment'' action and processing multiple shipments (either all shipments or only those you select). {br}

You can print a shipment confirmation for a particular shipment you are viewing on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] form by clicking '''Reports &gt; Print Shipment Confirmation''' on the form toolbar. For multiple shipments, you can print shipment confirmations by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_30_00|Process Shipments] form. For more details, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Shipment_Processing|Shipment Processing Steps].
==4. Prepare the Sales Orders Invoice==
You can prepare a Sales Orders invoice for a particular shipment you are viewing on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302000|SO302000]) form by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Prepare Invoice''' on the form toolbar. Alternatively, you can create multiple invoices on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_30_00|Process Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO503000|SO503000]) form by selecting the ''Prepare Invoice'' action and processing multiple shipments (either all shipments or only those you select). {br}

Any of the prepared Sales Orders invoices can be reviewed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. You can print a Sales Orders invoice by clicking '''Reports &gt; Print Invoice''' on the form toolbar of this form. 
==5. Release the Sales Orders Invoice==
To release the Sales Orders invoice, you click '''Actions &gt; Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. When the Sales Orders invoice is released, a batch of General Ledger transactions is generated. Also, when this invoice is released, the related Accounts Receivable invoice with the same reference number becomes available on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_10_00|Invoices and Memos] ([~/?ScreenId=AR301000|AR301000]) form. For more information on the further processing of Accounts Receivable invoices, see [HelpRoot_Financials\AR__MNG_InvoicesMemos|Processing Invoices].{br}

No inventory issue is generated on release of the Sales Orders invoice with non-stock items because these items are not tracked in inventory. ((({S:Hint}If you have prepared a sales order with mixed lines of items (stock or non-stock, or both) that require shipping and non-stock items that do not require shipping, the shipment prepared for the order includes only the items that require shipping, while the prepared Sales Orders invoice for the sales order lists all the items from it. The inventory issue generated on release of the sales order invoice includes only stock items because their quantities are tracked in inventory. 
)))
