In Acumatica ERP, if the ''Drop Shipments'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, you can create sales orders whose goods are intended for drop-shipping. Drop-shipping means that a customer orders the goods from your company, sends the payment for the order to your company, and receives the goods directly from one of your vendors. {br}
For a sales order that includes items intended for drop-shipping, the typical processing involves the actions and generated documents shown in the following diagram.[anchor|#fig_ygr_p4d_h5][anchor|#image_dc1_xyx_2t][image:UserGuide/Images/Sale_for_Dropship.png|popup|350px] The following sections describe in detail the processing steps shown in the diagram.{br}{TOC} ==1. Enter the Sales Order== For a sales order in which some or all items will be drop-shipped, you create a new sales order of the ''SO'' type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. Its reference number is generated according to the numbering sequence assigned to this order type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form, and the order is saved with the ''On Hold'' status by default if the '''Hold Documents on Entry''' check box is selected for this order type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] form. If the order is on hold, you should clear the '''Hold''' check box on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] form for the order so you can process it further. ==2. Mark the Line or Lines for Drop-Shipping== For each line of the sales order that is intended for drop-shipping, on the '''Document Details''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] form, you need to select the check box in the '''Mark for PO''' column and select ''Drop-Ship'' in the '''PO Source''' column. The system does not allocate stock items in inventory based on the quantities of goods and the document amounts on sales orders for drop-shipping. {br}
When you save a sales order with the ''Open'' status, for each sales order line that is marked for drop-shipping, a purchase request of the ''Drop-Ship'' type is generated in the system. You can review the purchase requests on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_50_50_00|Create Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO505000|PO505000]) form and generate drop-ship purchase orders based on these purchase requests. ==3. Create the Drop-Ship Purchase Order== Drop-ship purchase orders can be mass-generated for multiple sales orders or can be created one by one for each sales order. For the latter option, while viewing a sales order with lines for drop-shipping on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, you click '''Actions &gt; Create Purchase Order'''; this opens the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_50_50_00|Create Purchase Orders] form, on which you can create drop-ship purchase orders based on the drop-ship purchase requests that have been created for this sales order. On this form, you select the unlabeled check box next to the lines to be processed (which could include lines from the sales order you were working with or any other order), and click '''Process''' on the form toolbar to generate the purchase order or orders of the ''Drop-Ship'' type.((({S:Hint}As an alternative to the actions in the previous paragraph, you can create a purchase order of the ''Drop-Ship'' type manually on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form, and then return to the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] form and link each applicable sales order line to this drop-ship purchase order manually. To do this, on the '''Document Details''' tab, you click the needed sales order line, and click '''PO Link''' on the table toolbar. In the '''Purchasing Details''' dialog box, which the system opens, select the line of the drop-ship purchase order to which the sales order line has to be linked. ))) On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] form, you can print a purchase order you have created by clicking '''Reports &gt; Print Purchase Order''' on the form toolbar. ==4. Create the Purchase Receipt for the Drop-Ship Purchase Order== After you have received a confirmation that the customer has received the goods from the vendor, you prepare a purchase receipt for the drop-ship purchase order. For each separate drop-ship purchase order, while viewing the order on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form, you can click '''Actions &gt; Enter PO Receipt''' on the form toolbar to create the purchase receipt manually. {br}
Alternatively, you can create a receipt by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form, and add to it multiple purchase orders of the same vendor by clicking '''Add PO''' or '''Add PO Line''' on the table toolbar of the '''Document Details''' tab. You then add the needed purchase orders or separate purchase order lines in the dialog that opens. ==5. Release the Purchase Receipt== To release the purchase receipt, you click '''Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form. The system does not create an inventory receipt on release of the purchase receipt because the items are not received in inventory and are instead delivered directly to the customer. When you release the purchase receipt, the status of the drop-ship purchase order is changed to ''Closed''; the sales order becomes completed, because for drop-ship lines of sales orders, purchase receipts function as shipments do. ==6. Prepare the Accounts Payable Bill== If the '''Create Bill''' check box is selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form, when you released the purchase receipt, the system generated an Accounts Payable bill to the vendor of the drop-shipped stock items automatically. Otherwise, you need to prepare the bill manually: While you are viewing the applicable purchase receipt on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] form, you can click '''Actions &gt; Enter AP Bill''' on the form toolbar. ==7. Release the Accounts Payable Bill== To release the Accounts Payable bill, you click '''Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP301000|AP301000]) form. On release of the bill, a batch of General Ledger Transactions is generated. ==8. Create a Sales Orders Invoice== You can prepare a Sales Orders (SO) invoice to be sent to a customer by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Prepare Invoice''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] form while viewing the applicable sales order. Alternatively, you can create multiple invoices on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_10_00|Process Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO501000|SO501000]) form by specifying the ''Prepare Invoice'' action and processing multiple orders (all listed orders or only those you select). {br}
Any prepared SO invoice can be reviewed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. You can print an SO invoice by clicking '''Reports &gt; Print Invoice''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] form. ==9. Release the Sales Orders Invoice== To release the Sales Orders invoice, you click '''Actions &gt; Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] form. On release of the invoice, a batch of General Ledger transactions is generated, and the system automatically generates a corresponding inventory issue with the date and posting period of the invoice. {br}
Also, when the SO invoice is released, the related Accounts Receivable invoice with the same reference number is generated and can be viewed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_10_00|Invoices and Memos] ([~/?ScreenId=AR301000|AR301000]) form. For more information on processing Accounts Receivable invoices, see [HelpRoot_Financials\AR__MNG_InvoicesMemos|Processing Invoices]. ==10. Release the Inventory Issue== The generated inventory issue is released automatically if the '''Automatically Release IN Documents''' check box is selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_10_10_00|Sales Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SO101000|SO101000]) form. If this check box is cleared, you have to release the inventory issue manually by clicking '''Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_20_00|Issues] ([~/?ScreenId=IN302000|IN302000]) form. On release of the inventory issue, a batch of General Ledger transactions is generated. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Drop-Ship_Order_Flow|Drop-Ship Purchase Orders] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__CNF_OrderType_SO|SO Order Type (Sales Order)] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__CNF_OrderType_SA|SA Order Type (Sales Order with Allocation)]

Drop shipping is a type of sales order fulfillment in which the customers order goods from your company, receive them directly from a vendor (wholesaler or manufacturer), and send payments for the orders to your company. The quantities of stock items on completed drop-ship orders are not included in the quantities available at any warehouse of your company, and no data in the Inventory module is updated when the drop-ship orders are completed. {br}
With Acumatica ERP, you can create drop-ship orders for goods that should be delivered directly to a customer location. You can add the following types of items to drop-ship orders:[anchor|#ul_mdw_11x_p1b] *Stock items: The system automatically assigns the ''Goods for Drop-Ship'' line type to these items. *Non-stock items that have both the '''Require Receipt''' and '''Require Shipment''' check boxes selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202000|IN202000]) form: The system automatically assigns the ''Non-Stock for Drop-Ship'' line type to these items. *Non-stock items that have the '''Require Receipt''' check box selected and the '''Require Shipment''' check box cleared on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202000|IN202000]) form: The system automatically assigns the ''Non-Stock'' line type to these items. The ''Non-Stock'' lines do not need to be linked to a sales order document. ((({S:Hint}Kits cannot be drop-shipped, because they are manufactured in your company. ))) You can create drop-ship orders based on sales orders and on requisitions created for customers. {br}{TOC} ==Enabling Drop-Ship Orders== In Acumatica ERP, the functionality of drop-ship orders is available only if the ''Inventory'' and ''Drop Shipments'' features are enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. {br}
If the ''Multiple Warehouses'' and ''Multiple Warehouse Locations'' features are enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, before you start creating and processing drop-ship orders, make sure that the ''Drop Shipments'' feature is enabled and that each warehouse has a default location for drop-ship orders selected in the '''Drop-Ship Location''' box on the '''Location Table''' tab on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_40_00|Warehouses] ([~/?ScreenId=IN204000|IN204000]) form. Because specifying a warehouse and warehouse location is mandatory for all inventory documents, the system will automatically insert this location in all documents generated for drop-ship orders. ==Processing Different Line Types in Drop-Ship Orders== Drop-ship orders can include lines of different types. The type a particular line has depends on the settings of the item selected in the '''Inventory ID''' box; the system processes lines of different types in different ways. The following line types are available in drop-ship orders:[anchor|#ul_vpl_d5k_x1b] *''Goods for Drop-Ship'': The system assigns this line type to all stock items. Lines of this type are copied to purchase receipts, where each ''Goods for Drop-Ship'' line must be linked to a sales order document. *''Non-Stock for Drop-Ship'': The system assigns this line type to non-stock items that have both the '''Require Receipt''' and '''Require Shipment''' check boxes selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202000|IN202000]) form. Lines of this type are copied to purchase receipts, where each ''Non-Stock for Drop-Ship'' line must be linked to a sales order document. *''Non-Stock'': The system assigns this line type to non-stock items that have the '''Require Receipt''' check box selected and the '''Require Shipment''' check box cleared on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] form. The ''Non-Stock'' lines are copied to purchase receipts and do not need to be linked to a sales order document. *''Service'': The system assigns this line type to non-stock items that have the '''Require Receipt''' check box cleared on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] form, and to lines in which no '''Inventory ID''' is specified. The way the system processes ''Service'' lines in drop-ship orders depends on whether the '''Process Service Lines from Drop-Ship Purchase Orders via Purchase Receipt''' check box is selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_10_10_00|Purchase Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=PO101000|PO101000]) form. For more details, see the next section. *''Freight'': You can add a line without an '''Inventory ID''' specified and select this line type manually to record freight expenses for the order. Lines of this type are copied to purchase receipt, or could be added directly to purchase receipt, and do not need to be linked to a sales order document. The freight amount is posted to the Freight Expense account and subaccount specified on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_10_10_00|Purchase Orders Preferences] form. *''Description'': You can add a line without an '''Inventory ID''' specified and select this line type manually. These lines are used for informational purposes. Lines of this type are not copied to purchase receipts. ((({S:Hint}Kits cannot be drop-shipped, because they are manufactured in your company. ))) ==Processing Service Lines in Drop-Ship Orders== Depending on your business processes, you can select which workflow the system should use for processing ''Service'' lines. You select the needed workflow by using the '''Process Service Lines from Drop-Ship Purchase Orders via Purchase Receipt''' check box on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_10_10_00|Purchase Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=PO101000|PO101000]) form as follows:[anchor|#ul_qb5_mxk_x1b] *If the check box is selected, you can process ''Service'' lines through purchase receipts: When you create a purchase receipt for the drop-ship purchase order, the non-stock lines of the ''Service'' type that haven&rsquo;t been billed to the vendor yet are copied to the created purchase receipt. You cannot create an Accounts Payable bill for the ''Service'' lines for which the purchase receipt has not been created yet. Also, you can add lines of the ''Service'' type directly to purchase receipts without linking them to a purchase order and sales order. *:This setting gives you the ability to handle charges added by vendors of drop-ship orders when their goods are delivered to the customer. Your company will absorb these charges without again billing the customer for them. *If the check box is cleared (the default setting), processing ''Service'' lines doesn&rsquo;t involve creating a purchase receipt an Accounts Payable bill (or multiple bills) has to be created directly from the drop-ship order. These lines do not have to be linked to a sales order. *:((({S:Hint}When you create a purchase receipt for a purchase order with lines of different types, the system does not copy ''Service'' lines to a purchase receipt prepared from a purchase order. Also, ''Service'' lines cannot be added to the purchase receipt manually. )))
==Approving Drop-Ship Purchase Orders== Depending on the order processing flows established in your company, you use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_50_30_10|Approvals] ([~/?ScreenId=EP503010|EP503010]) form to approve drop-ship purchase orders and the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_50_30_00|Print/Email Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO503000|PO503000]) form to email them to vendors or to print them for sending by mail. Optionally, the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form can be used by the users involved in this processing because the '''Actions''' menu includes the '''Approve''', '''Email Purchase Order''', and '''Print Purchase Order''' menu commands. ==Creating a Purchase Receipt for a Drop-Ship Order== To create a receipt, you need a confirmation that the customer has received the goods or services from the vendor. This confirmation may be received through a call, an email, or another means. Based on the business routines established in your company, you can create purchase receipts when you receive invoices from the vendors or when you have heard from the customer, or you can create purchase receipts in advance and release them when you enter vendor invoices as bills. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Types_of_Purchase_Orders|Types of Purchase Orders] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Purchase_Receipt_Processing|Purchase Receipt Creation] *[HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_50_50_00|Create Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO505000|PO505000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_30_00|Process Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO503000|SO503000])

For a particular sales order that you are reviewing on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, you can create a drop-ship purchase order (or multiple drop-ship purchase orders) by mass-processing purchase requests of the ''Drop-Ship'' type related to this sales order on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_50_50_00|Create Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO505000|PO505000]).[anchor|#_d6e773c2-5eab-4c3f-b5a4-8fc49cbfea72]((({S:Hint}To open any form, you can navigate to it or search for it (by its name or by its form ID without periods). For more information about search capabilities, see [HelpRoot_Interface\UIG__con_New_UI_Search|Search in the Modern UI]. ))) ==To Create a Drop-Ship Purchase Order For a Particular Sales Order==[anchor|#_0c8d85f8-ea71-4260-a610-04f3b47ad03c] #Open the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form by searching for or navigating to it. #Select the order to be processed by specifying its type (''SO'' or a custom order type used in your organization for drop shipping) and its reference number. #On the form toolbar, click '''Actions &gt; Create Purchase Order'''. This opens the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_50_50_00|Create Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO505000|PO505000]) form with the list of purchase requests filtered for this particular sales order. #If needed, change the '''Creation Date''', which is the date on which the purchase order or orders will be generated. #In the table, select the unlabeled check boxes in the rows of the needed lines with the ''Drop-Ship'' type, and make sure each of the selected lines has the proper vendor specified in the '''Vendor''' box. # Click '''Process''' on the form toolbar, or click '''Process All''' to generate purchase orders for all listed lines. The system generates the drop-ship purchase orders.
