==Notes About the Procedure==[anchor|#_7f6113bc-0069-4560-bd12-5f89a03a089e] The notes in this section describe the nuances of the UI elements available on the form, such as when an element is required and when it is not, and when the system fills in settings by default. This section can include other notes.{br}
Note the following about creating drop-ship purchase orders for multiple sales orders:[anchor|#ul_ckv_tnv_tz] *To narrow the list of purchase requests shown on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_50_50_00|Create Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO505000|PO505000]) form, you can filter the list of sales orders by a product manager, product workgroup, item class, warehouse, or vendor (or more than one of these criteria). *You can link existing sales orders and drop-ship purchase orders. For instruction, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__How_Create_PO_for_SO|To Create a Drop-Ship Purchase Order with a Link to a Sales Order].

If your company sells items that are purchased only when sales orders for these items exist, each sales order may result in multiple purchase orders for different vendors, and each purchase order may include items from multiple sales orders. These factors make it difficult to track the fulfillment of sales orders.{br}

In Acumatica ERP, if the ''Sales Order to Purchase Order Link'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, you can easily link sales orders to existing purchase orders and receipts, to enable the tracking of sales order fulfillment. The system uses these links to allocate the items listed on purchase receipts for specific sales orders and to automate the creation of transfer orders, if needed. This functionality can be very helpful if you have multiple warehouses and perform purchasing only to particular larger warehouses (distribution centers)—the system will generate the required transfers between warehouses, and you can easily track where the particular sales order is in the fulfillment process.((({S:Hint}Sales order lines marked for purchase are not processed during the quick processing of a sales order. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Quick_Process_Workflow|Quick Processing of Sales Orders].
))){br}{TOC}
==Creating Sales Orders with Items Requested for Purchase==
If the quantity of an item added to a sales order is out of stock fully or partially, you can purchase the remaining quantity. You specify that the remaining quantity should be purchased for the order by selecting the '''Mark for PO''' check box for the line on the '''Document Details''' tab. The quantity initially allocated for the order remains allocated, while the quantity that must be purchased remains unallocated. Whether or not you can create partial shipments depends on the shipping rules specified for the orders lines and for the whole order. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Shipping_Rules|Shipping Rule Combinations]. {br}

Once you take the sales order off hold, the order appears on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_50_50_00|Create Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO505000|PO505000]) form and you can generate a purchase order which will be linked to the original sales order. Once receipts for the remaining quantities are released, you can allocate the initially unallocated quantities manually by using the '''Allocations''' dialog box on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. Even if the '''Replan Back-Orders''' check box is selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_10_10_00|Inventory Preferences], releasing inventory receipts does not update automatically plan types for sales orders with allocations (on release of receipts, the unallocated quantities still are shown as ''Back Ordered'' until you manually allocate them). 
==Linking Sales Orders to Purchase Orders==
If you need to promptly fulfill a sales order line for which the quantity of the item is insufficient, or if the sales order includes an item that is purchased only for specific sales orders, you can mark the applicable lines for purchasing—that is, select the check box in the''' Mark for PO''' column. Also, after you have shipped the available quantity of an item, you may need to order the remaining quantity that was unavailable at the time of shipping; in this case, you also can select the '''Mark for PO''' check box for the line. ((({S:Hint}In a sales order of the ''RR'' or ''RM'' type, only a line with the ''Issue'' operation can be marked for purchasing.
)))
You can include a sales order line that requires purchasing in a purchase order in one of the following ways:[anchor|#ul_xb1_rmt_wp]
*By using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form: Select the sales order line, and then click '''Create Purchase Order''' on the '''Actions''' menu on the form toolbar.
*By using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_50_50_00|Create Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO505000|PO505000]) form: Select multiple lines of different sales orders to create multiple purchase orders for these sales orders. The system consolidates the item quantities and group the items by vendor as needed.

You also can link the line of a sales order that has the '''Mark for PO''' check box selected to an existing purchase order that has not been completed yet. For instance, if you have created a new sales order that lists the same items as the existing purchase order does. If the purchase order has a quantity that exactly matches the total quantity on the sales orders that are already linked, you should first increase the quantity on the purchase order, and then link the sales order to this purchase order.
==Linking Purchase Receipts to Sales Orders==
The purchased items ordered in a sales order may be received to warehouses other than the warehouse specified on the sales order. If the users properly specify links between the purchase receipts and purchase orders, Acumatica ERP enables tracking of sales order fulfillment, reserves the received items for sales orders, and automates transfers of the items to the needed warehouses. {br}

To make it possible to track items from receipts to original sales orders, you need to link each receipt to the corresponding purchase order in one of the following ways:[anchor|#ul_hgm_m4p_wp]
*Open the purchase order on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form, and create a receipt for it by selecting '''Enter PO Receipt''' from the '''Actions''' menu on the form toolbar.
*Create a receipt on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form, and link all the related purchase orders to this new receipt by clicking '''Add PO''' or '''Add PO Line''' on the table toolbar.

To view the original sales orders linked to the purchase receipt, for each receipt line, click '''View PO''' on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] form. A dialog box opens that displays the list of sales orders that are linked to the purchase orders on which this receipt is based.{br}

After a receipt has been properly linked to all the related purchase orders, you will be able to track the stage of fulfillment for each line of the original sales order by clicking '''Allocations''' on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] form. In the '''Allocations''' dialog box, which opens, you can view an allocation that the system automatically performs to reserve the line item quantity required for the sale order on the purchase receipt. In the '''Allocations''' dialog box, you can also view the reference numbers of the related documents in the '''Related Documents''' column: the purchase order and the receipt. (You can click any reference number of a related document to view the document.){br}

If a purchase order line that corresponds to a sales order is completed or canceled, the system adds a new allocation line, which can be viewed in the '''Allocations''' dialog box on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] form. This line has the '''Mark for PO''' check box cleared and indicates that the shipment should be prepared for the item quantity in this line. When the shipment is confirmed for this line, the line is removed from the '''Allocations''' dialog box.{br}

On release of the receipt, the quantities of items required for the sales orders are deducted from the item quantities available for shipping. If items are received to a warehouse other than the warehouse specified on the sales order, the system will generate a transfer request, which you can use to create a transfer order by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] form for a single transfer order, or on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_90_00|Create Transfer Orders] form for multiple transfer orders. For details, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__How_Create_Transfer_Order|To Create a Transfer Order (TR)] and [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__How_Process_Multiple_TRs|To Create Shipments for Multiple Orders].

You can create a purchase order for a particular sales order with lines marked for purchasing by processing purchase requests of the ''SO to Purchase'' type related to this sales order on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_50_50_00|Create Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO505000|PO505000]).[anchor|#_fa9523cd-aa1b-4d75-8bf3-8742020be216]((({S:Hint}To open any form, you can navigate to it or search for it (by its name or by its form ID without periods). For more information about search capabilities, see [HelpRoot_Interface\UIG__con_New_UI_Search|Search in the Modern UI]. ))) ==To Create a Purchase Order for a Particular Sales Order==[anchor|#_bb956d05-ffbf-44e6-98cf-9517b4c7c8c1] #Open the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form by searching for or navigating to it. #Select the order to be processed by specifying its type and its reference number. #On the form toolbar, click '''Actions &gt; Create Purchase Order'''. This opens the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_50_50_00|Create Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO505000|PO505000]) form with the list of purchase requests filtered for this particular sales order. #If needed, change the '''Creation Date''', which is the date on which the purchase order or orders will be generated. #Select the unlabeled check boxes next to the needed lines with the ''SO to Purchase'' in the table, and make sure each of the selected lines has the proper vendor specified in the '''Vendor''' box. # Click '''Process''' on the form toolbar, or click '''Process All''' to generate purchase orders for all listed lines. The system generates the purchase orders.
==Notes About the Procedure==[anchor|#_9330acca-1147-45eb-a4ae-3b87f84df334] The notes in this section describe the nuances of the UI elements available on the form, such as when an element is required and when it is not, and when the system fills in settings by default. This section can include other notes.{br}
Note the following about this procedure:[anchor|#ul_ckv_tnv_tz] *To narrow the list of purchase requests shown on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_50_50_00|Create Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO505000|PO505000]) form, you can filter the list of sales orders by a product manager, product workgroup, item class, warehouse, vendor or order type. *You can link existing sales orders and purchase orders. For instruction, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__How_Create_PO_for_SO|To Create a Drop-Ship Purchase Order with a Link to a Sales Order].

A point-of-sale (POS) system is an electronic system that is used to record the sales, payments, and return transactions of a retail store. The POS system can be operated by a cashier or can be a self-service terminal where customers perform all operations by themselves. When a customer pays for goods and services, the POS system processes a direct sales invoice to record the sale (that is, an invoice that updates inventory without a sales order and a shipment being processed).{br}
For simplified processing of direct sales with the integration of an external POS system, the ''Advanced SO Invoices'' feature should be enabled in Acumatica ERP on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. With this feature enabled, a user can add stock items directly to a Sales Orders invoice without creating and processing the associated sales order and shipment.{br}{TOC} ==Entry of a Direct Sale== If the ''Advanced SO Invoices'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, a user can add lines with stock items directly to an invoice on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. With this feature enabled, the following columns, which should be filled in for a direct invoice, appear on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form:[anchor|#ul_ytb_1d4_xcb] *'''Warehouse ID''': This column is mandatory if the ''Multiple Warehouses'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form. *'''Location''': This column is mandatory if the ''Multiple Warehouse Locations'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form. *'''Lot/Serial Nbr.''' and '''Expiration Date''': These columns appear if the ''Lot and Serial Tracking'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form. If the item selected in the line is lot- or serial-tracked, these columns could be mandatory or optional, depending on the item settings. For a serialized item added to a direct invoice, for each serial number, the user should add a separate invoice line with this item and a quantity of 1. For more information on configuring and processing lot- and serial-tracked items, see [HelpRoot_InvMgmt\IN__con_Lot_and_Serial_Numbers|Lot and Serial Numbers]. ((({S:Hint}In sales invoices created from sales orders or shipments, the listed columns are automatically filled in by the system and are not available for editing. ))) ==Sales Lines Linked to a Sales Order== A sales line in an invoice (that is, a line that represents a sold rather than returned item) could be linked to a sales order or not linked to any order. If a line of the direct sales invoice is linked to an open line of a sales order, the release of the invoice functions as a shipment does for the linked sales order line: On release of the invoice, the system updates the '''Shipped Qty.''' in the sales order line based on the quantity specified in the invoice line, and inserts the reference number of the Sales Orders invoice on the '''Shipments''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. ==Return Lines in a Direct Sales Invoice== Return lines in an invoice are lines that represent returned rather than sold items. In direct invoices of the ''Invoice'', ''Credit Memo'', and ''Debit Memo'' type created on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form, lines with different signs (that is, sales and return lines) can be combined in one document. In this case, the inventory operation for the inventory document to be generated is defined on the line level. The lines with a positive quantity are processed in the usual way. The lines with a negative quantity are processed as lines of a reversing document (that is, the generated General Ledger batch contains the same transactions as it would in a reversing document). {br}
You can also link a return line to the original sales invoice. When a document with a return line is released, the system generates an inventory issue, with the date and posting period of the invoice, that returns the item to inventory. ==General Workflow and Related Documents== For a Sales Orders invoice created for processing a direct sale or return, the typical processing involves the actions and generated documents shown in the following diagram.[anchor|#_289a7ce2-cd9a-455f-a1c3-28e09c923dfc][anchor|#_3af062fe-0d5a-4426-87cd-a0bfc35e12db][image:UserGuide/Images/Direct_Sales_and_Returns.png|popup|400px] The following sections describe in detail the processing steps shown in the diagram.[anchor|#_318e9841-5481-4086-b5c4-45249f0eacd0] #''Entering a direct Sales Orders invoice'' #:You enter a direct Sales Orders invoice on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. For stock items to be sold, you specify the positive quantity in a line; lines with a negative quantity are processed as returns of the selected items. If the invoice is created with the ''On Hold'' status, you should clear the '''Hold''' check box for the invoice so you can process it further. #:You can print the SO invoice by clicking '''Reports &gt; Print Invoice''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] form. #''Releasing the direct SO invoice'' #:To release the SO invoice, you click '''Actions &gt; Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. When the SO invoice is released, a batch of General Ledger transactions is generated; also, the system automatically generates an inventory issue for the stock items with the date and posting period of the SO invoice. For sales lines in the invoice, the system creates inventory issue lines with the ''Invoice'' or ''Debit Memo'' transaction type that issue the items from inventory. For return lines in the invoice, the system creates inventory issue lines with the ''Credit Memo'' transaction type that add returned items to inventory. Also, after the SO invoice release, the related Accounts Receivable invoice becomes available for review on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_10_00|Invoices and Memos] ([~/?ScreenId=AR301000|AR301000]) form. #''Releasing the inventory issue'' #:The generated inventory issue is released automatically if the '''Automatically Release IN Documents''' check box is selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_10_10_00|Sales Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SO101000|SO101000]) form. If this check box is cleared, you have to release the inventory issue manually by clicking '''Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_20_00|Issues] ([~/?ScreenId=IN302000|IN302000]) form while viewing the issue. On release of the inventory issue, a batch of General Ledger Transactions is generated.
