Acumatica ERP gives you the flexibility to manage various types of customer returns. Depending on your company&rsquo;s return policies, you may need to perform a return for credit with receiving the returned items to inventory. For this purpose, you an use a return order for credit (that is, an order with the ''RC'' predefined order type). This topic describes the processing steps you need to perform, and the transactions generated during these steps.{br}
The processing of a return order for credit involves the actions generated documents shown in the following diagram. [anchor|#fig_ll4_m1b_kdb][anchor|#image_ml4_m1b_kdb][image:UserGuide/Images/Return_for_Credit_With_Receipt.png|popup|450px] The following sections describe in detail the processing steps shown in the diagram.{br}{TOC} ==1. Enter the Return Order for Credit== You create a new return order for credit is created on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. A reference number for the new return order is generated according to the numbering sequence assigned to this order type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form. If the order is created with the ''On Hold'' status, you should clear the '''Hold''' check box for the order to process it further. ==2. Link the Original Invoice Line to the Order== Each line in the return order of the ''RC'' order type can include a reference to the original invoice for which the return is performed. To add an item to be returned and include a link to original invoice, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, you click '''Add Invoice''' on the table toolbar of the '''Document Details''' tab and select the line of the needed invoice in the '''Add Invoice Details''' dialog box (which opens). If an item to be returned has a specific lot or serial number, you should select this particular item from the list of invoice lines.((({S:Hint}You can also add a stock item to be returned without linking it to an invoice. To do this, click '''Add Stock Item''' on the table toolbar of the '''Document Details''' tab, and select the item in the '''Inventory Lookup''' dialog box (which opens). ))) ==3. Prepare the Receipt== A receipt of the items returned to inventory is processed in the system as a shipment document with the ''Receipt'' operation type. To create a receipt (also referred to as an incoming shipment), you click '''Actions''' > '''Create Receipt''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. The prepared incoming shipment can be reviewed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302000|SO302000]) form. ==4. Confirm the Receipt== You can confirm an incoming shipment for a particular order by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Confirm Shipment''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302000|SO302000]) form; to confirm multiple incoming shipments, you can execute the '''Confirm Shipment''' action for the selected shipments on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_30_00|Process Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO503000|SO503000]) form. ==5. Prepare the Sales Orders Invoice== You prepare the Sales Orders invoice by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Prepare Invoice''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, or you can create invoices by running the ''Prepare Invoice'' action for multiple selected orders on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_10_00|Process Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO501000|SO501000]) form. {br}
The prepared document or documents of the ''Credit Memo'' type can be reviewed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. You can print a Sales Orders invoice by clicking '''Reports &gt; Print Invoice''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. ==6. Release the Sales Orders Invoice== To release the Sales Orders invoice, you click '''Actions &gt; Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. When the Sales Orders invoice is released, a batch of General Ledger transactions is generated. Also, when the SO invoice is released, the system automatically generates an inventory issue with the ''Credit Memo'' transaction type. Also, the related Accounts Receivable credit memo with the same reference number becomes available for reviewing on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_10_00|Invoices and Memos] ([~/?ScreenId=AR301000|AR301000]) form. ==7. Release the Inventory Issue== The generated inventory issue is released automatically if the '''Automatically Release IN Documents''' check box is selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_10_10_00|Sales Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SO101000|SO101000]) form. If this check box is cleared, you have to release the inventory issue manually by clicking '''Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_20_00|Issues] ([~/?ScreenId=IN302000|IN302000]) form. On release of the inventory issue, a batch of General Ledger transactions is generated.((({S:Hint}To finish the return process, you need to process the Accounts Receivable credit memo to completion. You can apply the credit memo to the original invoice, or process the customer refund if the original invoice was already paid. For details on credit memo application, see [HelpRoot_Financials\AR__how_Closing_a_Credit_Memo|To Apply a Credit Memo]. For details on processing of a customer refund, see [HelpRoot_Financials\AR__how_Issuing_a_Customer_Refund|To Issue a Refund]. ))) ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__CNF_OrderType_RC|RC Order Type (Return for Credit)] *[HelpRoot_Financials\AR__how_Closing_a_Credit_Memo|To Apply a Credit Memo] *[HelpRoot_Financials\AR__how_Issuing_a_Customer_Refund|To Issue a Refund] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__How_Enter_RC_Order|To Create a Return for Credit Order (RC)] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__How_Process_RC_Order|To Process a Return for Credit Order (RC)]

Acumatica ERP gives you the flexibility to manage various types of customer returns. Depending on your company&rsquo;s return policies, you may need to perform a return for credit when shipping of returned items to inventory is not needed. This topic describes the processing steps you need to perform, and the transactions generated during these steps.{br}
To process an unauthorized return without receipt and shipment, you can use a credit memo order (''CM''). The processing of a return for credit involves the actions and generated documents shown in the following diagram.[anchor|#fig_xqs_s4n_jdb][anchor|#image_sqs_xrk_3db][image:UserGuide/Images/Return_for_Credit_Without_Receipt.png|popup|400px] The following sections describe in detail the processing steps shown in the diagram.{br}{TOC} ==1. Enter the Credit Memo Order== You create a new credit memo order on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. A reference number for the new return order is generated according to the numbering sequence assigned to this order type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form. If the order is created with the ''On Hold'' status, you should clear the '''Hold''' check box for the order to process it further. ==2. Link the Original Invoice Line to the Order== Each line in the order of the ''CM'' order type can include a reference to the original invoice for which the return is performed. To add an item to be returned and include a link to original invoice, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, you can click '''Add Invoice''' on the table toolbar of the '''Document Details''' tab and select the line of the needed invoice in the '''Add Invoice Details''' dialog box (which opens). ((({S:Hint}You can also add a stock item to be returned without linking it to an invoice. To do this, click '''Add Stock Item''' on the table toolbar of the '''Document Details''' tab, and select the item in the '''Inventory Lookup''' dialog box (which opens). ))) ==3. Prepare the Sales Orders Invoice== You can prepare the Sales Orders (SO) invoice by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Prepare Invoice''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, or you can create any number of invoices by running the ''Prepare Invoice'' action for multiple selected orders on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_10_00|Process Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO501000|SO501000]) form. {br}
The prepared document or documents of the ''Credit Memo'' type can be reviewed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. You can print an SO invoice by clicking '''Reports &gt; Print Invoice''' on the form toolbar of this form. ==4. Release the Sales Orders Invoice== For the credit memo order, the released Sales Orders invoice acts as a shipment does: On release of the invoice, the system updates the '''Qty. on Shipments''' value in the order lines based on the quantity specified in the credit memo lines, and inserts the reference number of the Sales Orders credit memo on the '''Shipments''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form.{br}
When the SO invoice is released, a batch of General Ledger transactions is generated, and the system automatically generates an inventory issue with the ''Credit Memo'' transaction type that adds the returned item to inventory. Also, a corresponding Accounts Receivable credit memo is generated and becomes available for review on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_10_00|Invoices and Memos] ([~/?ScreenId=AR301000|AR301000]) form. ==5. Release the Inventory Issue== The generated inventory issue is released automatically if the '''Automatically Release IN Documents''' check box is selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_10_10_00|Sales Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SO101000|SO101000]) form. If this check box is cleared, you have to release the inventory issue manually by clicking '''Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_20_00|Issues] ([~/?ScreenId=IN302000|IN302000]) form. On release of the inventory issue, a batch of General Ledger Transactions is generated.((({S:Hint}To finish the return process, you need to process Accounts Receivable credit memo to completion. You can apply the credit memo to the original invoice, or process the customer refund if the original invoice was already paid. For details on credit memo application, see [HelpRoot_Financials\AR__how_Closing_a_Credit_Memo|To Apply a Credit Memo]. For details on the processing of a customer refund, see [HelpRoot_Financials\AR__how_Issuing_a_Customer_Refund|To Issue a Refund]. ))) ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__CNF_OrderType_CM|CM Order Type (Credit Memo)] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__How_Process_CM|To Process a Credit Memo Order (CM)] *[HelpRoot_Financials\AR__how_Closing_a_Credit_Memo|To Apply a Credit Memo] *[HelpRoot_Financials\AR__how_Issuing_a_Customer_Refund|To Issue a Refund]

Acumatica ERP gives you the flexibility to manage various types of customer returns. Depending on your company&rsquo;s return policies, you may need to perform a return of an inventory item for cash. This topic describes the processing steps you need to perform, and the transactions generated during these steps.{br}
To process a return for cash, you can use a return order for cash (that is, an order with the ''CR'' predefined order type). The processing of a return for cash involves the actions and generated documents shown in the following diagram.[anchor|#fig_xqs_s4n_jdb][anchor|#image_sqs_xrk_3db][image:UserGuide/Images/Return_for_Cash.png|popup|400px] The following sections describe in detail the processing steps shown in the diagram.{br}{TOC} ==1. Enter the Return Order for Cash == You create a new return order for cash on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. A reference number for the new return order for cash is generated according to the numbering sequence assigned to this order type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form. If the order is created with the ''On Hold'' status, you should clear the '''Hold''' check box to process it further. ==2. Link the Original Invoice Line to the Order== Each line in the order of the ''CR'' order type can include a reference to the original invoice for which the return is performed. To add an item to be returned with a link to the original invoice, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, you can click '''Add Invoice''' on the table toolbar of the '''Document Details''' tab and select the line of the needed invoice in the '''Add Invoice Details''' dialog box (which opens). If an item to be returned has a specific lot or serial number, you should select this particular item from the list of invoice lines.((({S:Hint}You can also add a stock item to be returned without linking it to an invoice. To do this, click '''Add Stock Item''' on the table toolbar of the '''Document Details''' tab, and select an item in the '''Inventory Lookup''' dialog box (which opens). ))) In each line added on the '''Document Details''' tab for an order of the ''CR'' type, you must specify a reason code. Also, the payment information on the '''Payment Settings''' tab is required for the cash return. ==3. Prepare the Sales Orders Invoice== You can prepare the Sales Orders (SO) invoice by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Prepare Invoice''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, or you can create multiple invoices by running the ''Prepare Invoice'' action for multiple selected orders on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_10_00|Process Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO501000|SO501000]) form. {br}
The prepared document or documents of the ''Cash Return'' type can be reviewed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. You can print an SO invoice by clicking '''Reports &gt; Print Invoice''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. ==4. Release the Sales Orders Invoice== When the Sales Orders invoice of the ''Cash Return'' type is released, the system automatically generates an inventory issue with the ''Credit Memo'' transaction type that adds the returned item to inventory; you can review the generated issue on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_20_00|Issues] ([~/?ScreenId=IN302000|IN302000]) form. Also, the related Accounts Receivable cash return with the same reference number becomes available for reviewing on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_40_00|Cash Sales] ([~/?ScreenId=AR304000|AR304000]) form. The document updates the appropriate sales and cash accounts. ==5. Release the Inventory Issue== The generated inventory issue is released automatically if the '''Automatically Release IN Documents''' check box is selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_10_10_00|Sales Orders Preferences] form. If this check box is cleared, you have to release the inventory issue manually by clicking '''Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_20_00|Issues] ([~/?ScreenId=IN302000|IN302000]) form. On release of the inventory issue, a batch of General Ledger Transactions is generated.

Acumatica ERP gives you the flexibility to manage various types of customer returns. Depending on your company&rsquo;s return policies, you may need to authorize a customer return in which the customer receives an exact replacement of a particular item or items. For this purpose, you can use a return order for replacement, and a printed or electronic copy of this document can be sent to the customer. The customer then returns the rejected goods according to this order, the goods are returned to inventory, and the customer receives a replacement for the rejected goods. This topic describes the processing steps you need to perform, and the transactions generated during these steps.{br}
To process a return for exact replacement, you use a return order for replacement (that is, an order with the ''RR'' predefined order type). The processing of a return order for replacement involves the actions and generated documents shown in the diagram below.[anchor|#_e16a8fa5-9988-4476-9d74-b81e91c36a16][image:UserGuide/Images/Return_for_Exact_Replacement.png|popup|450px] The following sections describe in detail the processing steps shown in the diagram.{br}{TOC} ==1. Enter the Return Order for Replacement== A new return order for replacement of the ''RR'' predefined type is created on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. A reference number for the new return order is generated according to the numbering sequence assigned to this order type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form. If the order is created with the ''On Hold'' status, you should clear the '''Hold''' check box for the order to process it further. ==2. Link the Original Invoice Line to the Order== Each return line in the order of the ''RR'' order type can include a reference to the original Sales Orders invoice for which the return is performed. To add an item to be returned and include a link to original invoice, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, you can click '''Add Invoice''' on the table toolbar of the '''Document Details''' tab and select the line of the needed invoice in the '''Add Invoice Details''' dialog box (which opens). ((({S:Hint}You can also add a stock item to be returned without linking it to an invoice. To do this, click '''Add Stock Item''' on the table toolbar of the '''Document Details''' tab, and select the item in the '''Inventory Lookup''' dialog box (which opens). ))) ==3. Add a Line with the Item for Replacement== An added return line (linked or not linked to an invoice) has the ''Receipt'' operation specified in the '''Operation''' column. Each line with the ''Receipt'' operation type in an ''RR'' order should have a corresponding line with the ''Issue'' operation type for a replacement item. If the item in a ''Receipt''-type line is not tracked by serial or lot numbers, you can select the '''Auto-Create Issue''' check box for the line; then (when the shipment is confirmed) the system will automatically add the corresponding ''Issue''-type lines with the details copied from the ''Receipt''-type lines. If the items to be returned have specific lot or serial numbers, clear the '''Auto-Create Issue''' check box for the line, and add an ''Issue''-type line for the replacement line manually. ==4. Prepare the Receipt== A receipt of the items returned to inventory is processed in the system as a shipment document with the ''Receipt'' operation type. To create a receipt (also referred to as an incoming shipment), you click '''Actions''' > '''Create Receipt''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. The prepared incoming shipment can be reviewed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302000|SO302000]) form. ==5. Confirm the Receipt== You can confirm an incoming shipment for a particular order by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Confirm Shipment''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302000|SO302000]) form; to confirm multiple incoming shipments, you can execute the ''Confirm Shipment'' action for the selected shipments on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_30_00|Process Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO503000|SO503000]) form. ==6. Prepare the Shipment with the Replacement Item== You prepare the shipment with the ''Issue'' operation type by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Create Shipment''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. Alternatively, you can use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_10_00|Process Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO501000|SO501000]) form to create shipments for multiple orders by executing the ''Create Shipment'' action for the selected return orders. The prepared shipment can be reviewed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302000|SO302000]) form.{br}
You can print a pick list for a particular shipment by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] form. For multiple shipments with the ''On Hold'' and ''Open'' statuses, you can print pick lists by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_30_00|Process Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO503000|SO503000]) form. For more details, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Shipment_Processing|Shipment Processing Steps]. ==7. Confirm the Shipment== You can confirm a shipment for a particular order by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Confirm Shipment''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302000|SO302000]) form; to confirm multiple shipments, you can execute the ''Confirm Shipment'' action for the selected shipments on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_30_00|Process Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO503000|SO503000]) form. ==8. Update Inventory== You can update inventory for each shipment separately by opening the shipment on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302000|SO302000]) form and clicking '''Actions''' > '''Update IN''' to generate the appropriate inventory transaction and to update the item availability data. Alternatively, you can use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_30_00|Process Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO503000|SO503000]) form to update inventory by executing the ''Update IN'' action for the selected shipments.{br}
Notice that Sales Orders invoices and Accounts Receivable invoices are not generated for an ''RR'' order because the returned item is replaced with another item with no price changes. ==9. Release the Inventory Issues== The generated inventory issues are released automatically if the '''Automatically Release IN Documents''' check box is selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_10_10_00|Sales Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SO101000|SO101000]) form. If this check box is cleared, you have to release the inventory issues manually by clicking '''Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_20_00|Issues] ([~/?ScreenId=IN302000|IN302000]) form for each of the inventory issues. On release of the inventory issues, batches of General Ledger transactions are generated.

Acumatica ERP gives you the flexibility to manage various types of customer returns. Depending on your company&rsquo;s return policies, you may need to perform a merchandise authorization return of an inventory item for possible credit and replacement. For this purpose, you an use a merchandise authorization return order, and you can send the customer a printed or electronic copy of it along with the goods to be returned. Once the goods are received by your organization, they are returned to inventory, and the customer receives other goods instead. For this type of return order, different items than those returned may be included for replacement, freight and shipping and handling charges may be included, and the items could be returned at higher or lower prices. {br}
To process a merchandise authorization return, you can use a return order of the ''RM'' predefined order type. The processing of a ''RM'' order (further in this topic referred to as a ''return order'') involves the actions and generated documents shown in the following diagram.[anchor|#_01f4db7a-e906-4749-beab-6c47fdb8a97d][image:UserGuide/Images/Generic_Authorized_Return.png|popup|450px] The following sections describe in detail the processing steps shown in the diagram.{br}{TOC} ==1. Enter the Merchandise Return Order== You create a new return order of the ''RM'' order type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. A reference number for the new return order is generated according to the numbering sequence assigned to this order type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form. If the order is created with the ''On Hold'' status, you should clear the '''Hold''' check box for the order to process it further. ==2. Link the Original Invoice Line to the Order== Each return line in an order of the ''RM'' order type could include a reference to the original invoice for which the return is performed. To add an item to be returned and include a link to the original invoice, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, you can click '''Add Invoice''' on the table toolbar of the '''Document Details''' tab and select the line of the needed invoice in the '''Add Invoice Details''' dialog box (which opens). ((({S:Hint}You can also add a stock item to be returned without linking it to an invoice. To do this, click '''Add Stock Item''' on the table toolbar of the '''Document Details''' tab, and select the item in the '''Inventory Lookup''' dialog box (which opens). ))) An added return line (whether or not it is linked to an invoice) has the ''Receipt'' operation specified in the '''Operation''' column. After you have added the ''Receipt'' lines, make sure that the '''Auto-Create Issue''' check box is cleared in these lines (because you need to add replacement items and specify their details manually). ==3. Add a Line with the Item for Replacement== Each line with the ''Receipt'' transaction type in an ''RM'' order should have a corresponding line with the ''Issue'' operation type for a replacement item. You need to add an ''Issue''-type line for the replacement lines manually. Alternatively, if the returned item is not tracked by serial or lot numbers, and the item price wasn&rsquo;t changed between the original sale and return, you can select the '''Auto-Create Issue''' check box for the line; on shipment confirmation, the system will add the corresponding ''Issue''-type lines automatically and copy the line details from the ''Receipt''-type lines. ==4a–4b. Process the Return and the Replacement== To complete the order, you need to process the receipt of the returned item and the shipment of the replacement item. You can process the return and replacement in any order on its own, or you can process multiple returns and replacements simultaneously on mass-processing forms. You perform the following general steps for processing: [anchor|#_228a8628-2ef3-4115-aaae-ce8fbd6b3cec] #Prepare the receipt (for return) and the shipment (for replacement) by doing the following: #*You prepare the receipt (that is, the incoming shipment with the ''Receipt'' operation type) by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Create Receipt''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. #*You prepare the outgoing shipment with the ''Issue'' operation type by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Create Shipment''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] form. #:The prepared shipment can be reviewed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302000|SO302000]) form. #:Alternatively, you can use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_10_00|Process Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO501000|SO501000]) form to create both incoming and outgoing shipments for one order or multiple orders. To do this, you select the ''Create Shipment'' action, select the needed orders, and click '''Process''' on the form toolbar. #Confirm the receipt and the shipment. #:You can confirm a particular receipt or shipment by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Confirm Shipment''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] form; to confirm multiple shipments, you can select the ''Confirm Shipment'' action, select the needed shipments, and click '''Process''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_30_00|Process Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO503000|SO503000]) form. #Prepare the Sales Orders invoices. #:You prepare the Sales Orders invoice for a particular receipt or shipment by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Prepare Invoice''' on the form toolbar on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] form, or you can create invoices by processing the ''Prepare Invoice'' action for multiple selected shipments on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_30_00|Process Shipments] form. #:The prepared document or documents can be reviewed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. For the return, the system generates a Sales Orders invoice of the ''Credit Memo'' type; for the shipment, the system generates a Sales Orders invoice of the ''Invoice'' type. #:You can print a Sales Orders invoice by clicking '''Reports &gt; Print Invoice''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] form. #Release the Sales Orders invoices. #:When the Sales Orders invoices are released, the system automatically generates two inventory issues: one with the ''Return'' transaction type for the return, and one with the ''Issue'' transaction type for replacement. Also, the related Accounts Receivable credit memo and invoice with the same reference numbers become available for reviewing on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_10_00|Invoices and Memos] ([~/?ScreenId=AR301000|AR301000]) form. #:Once you release the Sales Orders invoices, the original ''RM'' order is assigned the ''Completed'' status. #Release the generated inventory issues. #:The generated inventory issues are released automatically if the '''Automatically Release IN Documents''' check box is selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_10_10_00|Sales Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SO101000|SO101000]) form. If this check box is cleared, you have to release each inventory issue manually by clicking '''Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_20_00|Issues] ([~/?ScreenId=IN302000|IN302000]) form. On release of each inventory issue, a batch of the General Ledger transactions is generated.
==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__How_Process_RM_Order|To Process a Merchandise Authorization Return Order (RM)]

Many businesses perform sales on credit: A customer order is paid after the order has been shipped and an invoice for the shipped goods and services has been sent to the customer. In some cases, businesses may require prepayments or payments to be made for particular orders, or your organization can charge a customer card for specific orders. If you rely on payment auto-application, payments are applied to unrelated invoices starting from the earliest documents, and it is difficult to perform reconciliation of balances later.{br}

With Acumatica ERP, you can create payments and prepayments directly on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, thus reserving these payments or prepayments for the particular order in full or partially. Also, you can link an order to existing prepayments or payments by their reference numbers. There may be many variations of processing a sales order with reserved payment, such as multiple shipments and multiple invoices for the order, multiple payments reserved for one order, or multiple orders paid by one prepayment. If the order is being shipped in multiple shipments, you can track how the payment's partial amounts was applied to multiple invoices.{br}{TOC}
==Linking Orders and Payments==
When you enter a new sales order on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, you can create a payment or prepayment directly from the '''Payments''' tab by clicking '''Create Payment''' or '''Create Prepayment''' on the table toolbar. The system brings up the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_20_00|Payments and Applications] ([~/?ScreenId=AR302000|AR302000]) form in a pop-up window. After you enter and save the payment or prepayment, it is linked to the sales order and can be reviewed on the '''Payments''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders]form. {br}

When you enter a new customer prepayment or payment on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_20_00|Payments and Applications] form, you can link it directly to a particular order or multiple by adding the order or orders on the '''Orders to Apply''' tab. Payments with balances that have been partially applied to invoices (whether or not the invoices are related to the order) can also be reserved for sales orders. {br}

For customers who pay by using credit cards, you can create a payment, link it to particular sales order or orders, and charge the credit card by using the same form, [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_20_00|Payments and Applications]. 
==Applying Parent and Child Payments==
If the ''Parent-Child Customer Relationship'' feature has been enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, you can configure parent-child relationships between customer accounts. If the '''Consolidate Balance''' check box is selected for a child account on the '''Billing Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_30_00|Customers] ([~/?ScreenId=AR303000|AR303000]) form, you can apply parent payments and prepayments to the open sales orders of this child account. When the invoice is prepared for the sales order, the payment application amount is transferred to the invoice. If you enter an invoice for a child customer directly on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form, you can also apply payments and prepayments of the parent customer to this invoice. {br}

For more information on the configuration of parent-child relationships, see [HelpRoot_Financials\AR__MNG_ParentChild|Managing Parent-Child Relationships].
==Processing Orders with Reserved Payments==
An order with a payment linked is processed in the same way as any other order is. Once an order with linked payments or prepayments is shipped, the payment or prepayment amount applied to an order is transferred to the Sales Orders invoice or invoices generated for the order. On release of the SO invoices, the system applies the payment amounts reserved for the order to the invoices. If the amount of payments is equal to the order total, the invoices are closed. If the total amount of payments or prepayments applied to the order is less than the order total, the system leaves one of the invoices open with the unpaid balance (which is the difference between the order total and the payments&rsquo; total). {br}

You can view the history of application on the '''Application History''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_20_00|Payments and Applications] ([~/?ScreenId=AR302000|AR302000]) form. As orders linked to this payment are shipped and completed, you will see on the '''Application History''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_20_00|Payments and Applications] form the list of applied invoices (generated for those orders) as it is populated.{br}

When a full-amount payment has been reserved for an order, once the order has been shipped and an invoice has been generated and released, the payment amount is applied to the invoice; the invoice is assigned the ''Closed'' status on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form, while the order is assigned the ''Completed'' status on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. If an order with a full-amount payment is shipped partially and then is completed or canceled, the amount applied to the order is reset to zero, while the payment with an unapplied balance is assigned the ''Open'' status and its applied amount is transferred to the invoice. 
==Limitations on Payment Application==
The application of payments to sales orders has the following limitations:[anchor|#_9e2822e1-9e57-4355-ad92-76a923ec3658]
*Payments and prepayments can be applied to only sales orders with single-installment credit terms specified in the '''Terms''' box on the '''Financial Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. If you change single-installment credit terms to multiple-installment terms for an existing sales order with payments or prepayments applied, these applications will be unlinked from the sales order. For more information on configuring credit terms, see [HelpRoot_Financials\AR__con_Credit_Terms|Setup of Credit Terms].
*If approval of sales orders is required in your organization, you can specify payments for only orders that have undergone the required approvals and have the ''Open'' status. For details about approval processes, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Approvals|Sales Order Approval].

==Canceling Payment Reservation==
If no invoice has been generated for the order, you can cancel payment application by removing the reserved payment from the list on the '''Payments''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form.
