When purchase receipts are created and released, they indicate that the purchased goods have been received at the company&rsquo;s warehouses and allocated. In most cases, the purchasing process is completed when goods are received, and AP bills are released to adjust your outstanding balances with the vendors. In some organizations, the AP bill is processed before the items are received.{br}

Different organizations can use different workflow for the processing of purchases. The topics of this part of the guide provide a detailed description of the workflows that you can establish in Acumatica ERP for processing purchases.{br}{TOC}
