row.column:
To process a purchase of items in Acumatica ERP, you create and process purchase orders of the ''Normal'' type. In Acumatica ERP, you can process purchases in which the bills are generated after the ordered goods and services have been received from the vendors. {br}
The following diagram represents the general workflow of the processing of a purchase receipt before the bill is generated. [anchor|#_81d8c218-8f3a-4d5b-83f0-73c461393634][anchor|#_313a6c88-2601-4ed8-b70d-0cb493b80ab7][image:UserGuide/Images/PO_Receipt_Before_Bill.png|popup|450px] The remaining sections of this topic describe in detail the processing steps shown in the diagram.{br}{TOC} ==1. Enter the Purchase Order== You create a new purchase order of the ''Normal'' type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form. On the purchase order, you can list the stock and non-stock items to be purchased from the particular vendor. The reference number for a new purchase order is generated in accordance with the numbering sequence specified on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_10_10_00|Purchase Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=PO101000|PO101000]) form. If the order is initially created with the ''On Hold'' status, you should clear the '''Hold''' check box when you are ready to process the order further. For details about the settings specified in the purchase order, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Purchase_Order_Processing|Purchase Order Creation]. ==2. Prepare the Purchase Receipt== While you are viewing the purchase order on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form, you can create a purchase receipt for the purchase order by clicking '''Actions &gt; Enter PO Receipt''' on the form toolbar. The system navigates to the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form with the prepared purchase receipt. The reference number for the new purchase receipt is generated in accordance with the numbering sequence specified on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_10_10_00|Purchase Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=PO101000|PO101000]) form. If the purchase receipt is initially created with the ''On Hold'' status, you should clear the '''Hold''' check box when you are ready to process the receipt further.{br}
As an alternate way to prepare the purchase receipt, you can create a new purchase receipt of the ''Receipt'' type manually on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] form and add the lines of the purchase order (or of multiple purchase orders with the same vendor) to the purchase receipt. ==3. Release the Purchase Receipt== To release the prepared purchase receipt, while you are viewing it on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form, you click '''Release''' on the form toolbar. Alternatively, you can release multiple purchase receipts at the same time by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_50_10_00|Release Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO501000|PO501000]) form. {br}
When the purchase receipt is released, the system automatically generates a corresponding inventory receipt, with the date and posting period of the purchase receipt, to add the received items to inventory. You can review the generated inventory receipt on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_10_00|Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=IN301000|IN301000]) form.{br}
After all the lines in the purchase order have been received in full, the purchase order is assigned the ''Completed'' status. ==3. Prepare and Release the Accounts Payable Bill== If the '''Create Bill''' check box is selected for the purchase receipt on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form, when you release the purchase receipt, the system generates an accounts payable bill to the vendor automatically. Otherwise, you need to prepare the bill manually from the related purchase receipt by clicking '''Actions &gt; Enter AP Bill''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] form. You can view the generated AP bill on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP301000|AP301000]) form. {br}
Alternatively, you can create a new AP bill manually on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] form and add or link the lines of the purchase orders (for non-stock items that do not require purchase receipts) or purchase receipts (for stock items and non-stock items requiring receipt) to the bill. For more information on the processing of Accounts Payable bills, see [HelpRoot_Financials\AP_MNG_BillsAndAdjustments|Processing Bills and Adjustments].((({S:Hint}To be able to link the lines of a bill to the lines of the corresponding purchase orders and purchase receipts, make sure that for the bill, the ''Tax Settings'' option is selected in the '''Tax Calculation Mode''' box on the '''Financial Details''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] form. ))) If all the lines in the purchase order have been billed in full, the purchase order is assigned the ''Closed'' status. For more information on the rules that affect line closing and completion, see the topics of the [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_LineTypes|Line Types in Purchase Orders] section. ==4. Release the Inventory Receipt== The generated inventory receipt is released automatically if the '''Release IN Documents Automatically''' check box is selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_10_10_00|Purchase Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=PO101000|PO101000]) form. If this check box is cleared, you have to release the inventory receipt manually by clicking '''Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_10_00|Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=IN301000|IN301000]) form. On release of the inventory receipt, a batch of GL transactions is generated. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_AffectingProcessingDocs|Changing the Processing of Purchase Documents] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Managing_Order_Lines|Managing Lines in Purchase Documents] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_scn_Purchase_with_Bill_Before_Receipt|Purchase with Billing Before Receipt] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_scn_Direct_Purchase_Receipt|Purchase with Direct Purchase Receipt]

In your organization, if bills are received from vendors and entered into the system before the goods arrive or if bills are imported from a third-party system, you can establish a workflow in which the accounts payable bill can be processed before the ordered items have been received. {br}

You can create an AP bill before purchase receipt if the '''Allow AP Bill Before Receipt''' check box is selected for the applicable purchase order on the '''Other Information tab''' of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] form. The state of this check box is copied from the settings of the specified vendor on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_30_00|Vendors] ([~/?ScreenId=AP303000|AP303000]) form or from the settings of the particular vendor location on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_30_10|Vendor Locations] ([~/?ScreenId=AP303010|AP303010]) form. {br}

For the purchase orders that have the '''Allow AP Bill Before Receipt''' check box selected, you can process the AP bill and purchase receipt in any order. This topic describes the workflow with processing a bill before the related purchase receipt. For a description of the workflow with processing a receipt before the related bill, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_scn_Purchase_with_Receipt|Purchase with Receipt Before Billing].{br}

The following diagram represents the general workflow of the processing when billing occurs before the purchase receipt. [anchor|#_dab4f88c-1730-4b36-92d3-ac60fcfa5f7b][anchor|#_08aa5968-65b8-47e7-9754-5f7602c62929][image:UserGuide/Images/PO_Bill_Before_Receipt.png|popup|450px]
The remaining sections of this topic describe in detail the processing steps shown in the diagram.{br}{TOC}
==1. Enter the Purchase Order==
You create a new purchase order of the ''Normal'' type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form. On the purchase order, you can list the stock and non-stock items to be purchased from the particular vendor. The reference number for a new purchase order is generated in accordance with the numbering sequence specified on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_10_10_00|Purchase Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=PO101000|PO101000]) form. If the order is initially created with the ''On Hold'' status, you should clear the '''Hold''' check box when you are ready to process the order further. {br}

For details about the settings specified in the purchase order, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Purchase_Order_Processing|Purchase Order Creation].
==2. Prepare and Release the Accounts Payable Bill==
You prepare the accounts payable bill from a purchase order you are viewing on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form by clicking '''Actions &gt; Enter AP Bill''' on the form toolbar. You can view the generated AP bill on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP301000|AP301000]) form. {br}

Alternatively, you can create a new AP bill manually on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] form and add the lines of the purchase order to the bill by clicking '''Add PO''' on the table toolbar of the '''Document Details''' tab; you then select the needed purchase order in the dialog box that opens. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Linking_Bills|Accounts Payable Bills with Stock Items].{br}

You can release the generated bill at any moment, before or after the processing of the receipt of the ordered items. For more information on the processing of AP bills, see [HelpRoot_Financials\AP_MNG_BillsAndAdjustments|Processing Bills and Adjustments].
==3. Prepare the Purchase Receipt==
While you are viewing a purchase order on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form, you create the corresponding purchase receipt by clicking '''Actions &gt; Enter PO Receipt''' on the form toolbar. The system navigates to the prepared purchase receipt on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form. The reference number for the new purchase receipt is generated in accordances with the numbering sequence specified on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_10_10_00|Purchase Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=PO101000|PO101000]) form. If the purchase receipt is initially created with the ''On Hold'' status, you should clear the '''Hold''' check box when you are ready to process the purchase receipt further.{br}

As an alternate way to prepare the purchase receipt, you can create a new purchase receipt of the ''Receipt'' type manually on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] form and add the lines of the purchase order (or of multiple purchase orders with the same vendor) to the purchase receipt. {br}

If all the lines in the purchase order have been received and billed in full, the purchase order is assigned the ''Closed'' status. For more information on the rules that affect line closing and completion, see the topics of the [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_LineTypes|Line Types in Purchase Orders] section.
==4. Release the Purchase Receipt==
Because the AP bill has been already prepared, clear the '''Create Bill''' check box in the purchase receipt (if it was selected by default) before you release the purchase receipt. To release the prepared purchase receipt, while you are viewing it on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form, you click '''Release''' on the form toolbar. Alternatively, you can release multiple purchase receipts at the same time by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_50_10_00|Release Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO501000|PO501000]) form.{br}

When the purchase receipt is released, the system automatically generates a corresponding inventory receipt with the date and posting period of the purchase receipt to add the received items to inventory. You can view the generated inventory receipt on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_10_00|Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=IN301000|IN301000]) form.
==5. Release the Inventory Receipt==
The generated inventory receipt is released automatically if the '''Release IN Documents Automatically''' check box is selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_10_10_00|Purchase Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=PO101000|PO101000]) form. If this check box is cleared, you have to release the inventory receipt manually by clicking '''Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_10_00|Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=IN301000|IN301000]) form. On release of the inventory receipt, a batch of GL transactions is generated.
