The purchase process typically starts with an employee entering a purchase order. This topic describes how you create a purchase order, which settings could affect the purchase order processing, which lines could be added to the order, and how to track unbilled quantities and amounts in the order.{br}{TOC} ==Creating a Purchase Order== In general, the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form is the starting point for creating a purchase order, and employees can use this form to track the processing of the order. In Acumatica ERP, for processing most purchases, purchase orders of the ''Normal'' type are used. When you are creating a new order, you should first select a vendor and the vendor location. {br}
A newly created purchase order has the ''On Hold'' status. To reduce input errors on order entry, you can set up the validation of order totals by selecting the '''For Normal and Standard Orders''' check box in the '''Validate Total on Entry''' section of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_10_10_00|Purchase Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=PO101000|PO101000]) form. If this check box is selected, then when you create a new purchase order on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form, to take the order off hold, you must enter the order total in the '''Control Total''' box after verifying the order details. For more information on how you can set up document processing, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_AffectingProcessingDocs|Changing the Processing of Purchase Documents].((({S:Hint}Purchase orders based on requisitions, customer drop-ship orders, customer orders marked for purchasing, and replenishment requests can be created in bulk on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_50_50_00|Create Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO505000|PO505000]) form. ))) ==Adding Lines to a Purchase Order== In a purchase order created on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form, you list the stock and non-stock items to be purchased from the particular vendor. Purchase orders can include multiple lines of different line types. You can add stock items by clicking the '''Add Item''' button on the table toolbar of the '''Document Details''' tab and selecting from only the vendor&rsquo;s items or from the entire list of stock items. If you want to add non-stock items of any type (''Labor'', ''Service'', ''Non-Stock'', or ''Expense''), you can add a line and select a non-stock item by its inventory ID. The system processes different line types in different ways, which are described in detail in the following topics:[anchor|#_c005c8df-2e2d-420a-ac52-56479d9ec2a2] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Purchase_of_Stock|Stock Item Lines in Purchase Orders] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Purchase_of_NStock_w_Receipt|Non-Stock Lines in Purchase Orders] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Purchase_of_Services|Service Lines in Purchase Orders]
If a purchase order includes stock and non-stock items of various types, its processing includes the creation of a receipt or multiple receipts. Then you can create separate bills: one based on receipts linked to the order, and another based on those lines of the original purchase order whose line items do not require receipt. Alternatively, you can create a single bill for all purchase order lines, both stock and non-stock by manually adding the items not requiring receipt to a bill prepared based on a receipt. ((({S:Hint}If the ''Blanket and Standard Purchase Orders'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, you can also add a blanket purchase order or a line of a blanket purchase order to a purchase order. ))) ==Approving a Purchase Order== If the approval of purchase orders is configured in your system, the order is given the ''Pending Approval'' status once you take it off hold; the status will change to ''Pending Printing'', ''Pending Email'', or ''Open'' once all the assigned approvers approve it. For details on approval, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Purchase_Order_Approvals|Purchase Order Approval]. {br}
If the approval of purchase orders is not configured, a purchase order may need to be emailed or printed once you take it off hold. After that, the order is given the ''Open'' status and can be processed. ==Variations in Processing a Purchase Order == The general workflow of processing a purchase order with lines of any type is to process a purchase receipt (if one is needed) before creating an AP bill. However, if you receive bills from a particular vendor before the ordered items are received to inventory, you can configure this vendor so that for the purchase orders of this vendor, you can create and process an AP bill even before the purchase receipt is created for the purchase order. {br}
The order in which you create and process documents related to a purchase order depends on the state of the '''Allow AP Bill Before Receipt''' check box specified for a purchase order on the '''Other Information''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form. The state of this check box is copied from the vendor settings on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_30_00|Vendors] ([~/?ScreenId=AP303000|AP303000]) form, or from the vendor location settings on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_30_10|Vendor Locations] ([~/?ScreenId=AP303010|AP303010]) form. The setting affects the processing of purchase orders in the following way:[anchor|#_3b7eb647-9682-4cc4-8d99-3e0d9e8d839e] *If the check box is cleared, the AP bill can be created for a purchase order only after the related purchase receipt has been released. You can add to the created bill only unbilled lines of the released purchase receipts (for stock items and non-stock items requiring receipt) and unbilled purchase order lines (for non-stock items that do not require receipt). *If the check box is selected, the AP bill and purchase receipt can be prepared in any order. If the AP bill is prepared first, you can add to it unbilled lines of a purchase order that have not yet been included in any other bill.
For a detailed description of processing steps in these workflows, see the following topics:[anchor|#_3a0e87ab-2ddd-43d9-b71e-a6e4f8ae429f] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_scn_Purchase_with_Receipt|Purchase with Receipt Before Billing] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_scn_Purchase_with_Bill_Before_Receipt|Purchase with Billing Before Receipt]
