*[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Purchase_of_NStock_w_Receipt|Non-Stock Lines in Purchase Orders]
*[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Purchase_of_Services|Service Lines in Purchase Orders]

For each non-stock item, you define whether a purchase receipt is required by selecting or clearing the '''Require Receipt''' check box on the '''General Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202000|IN202000]) form. This setting affects the processing of non-stock items that are included in purchase orders. In a purchase order line on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form, when you select a non-stock item that requires a receipt, the system inserts ''Non-Stock'' as the line type.{br}
Processing a purchase order with ''Non-Stock'' lines always involves creating a receipt (or multiple receipts if the ordered items are not delivered at the same time). When you create a purchase receipt for a purchase order, the system copies all ''Non-Stock'' lines to the purchase receipt. {br}
This topic describes how the system processes purchase order lines for non-stock items requiring receipt.{br}{TOC} ==Processing of the Accounts Payable Bill for the Purchase Order== The general workflow of processing purchase orders with lines of any type is to process the associated purchase receipt (if one is needed) before the creation of the associated AP bill (see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_scn_Purchase_with_Receipt|Purchase with Receipt Before Billing] for details). However, if you receive bills from a particular vendor before the purchased items are received to inventory, you can configure this vendor so that for its purchase orders, you can create and process an AP bill before the purchase receipt is released. {br}
To do this, you need to select the '''Allow AP Bill Before Receipt''' check box in the vendor settings on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_30_00|Vendors] ([~/?ScreenId=AP303000|AP303000]) form; in addition, you can select this check box for a particular vendor location on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_30_10|Vendor Locations] ([~/?ScreenId=AP303010|AP303010]) form. The state of this check box will be copied to each purchase order created to this vendor, and can be reviewed on the '''Other Information''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form. For a detailed description on how to process a purchase order with the associated bill being prepared before the receipt, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_scn_Purchase_with_Bill_Before_Receipt|Purchase with Billing Before Receipt]. ==Posting Accounts for Non-Stock Lines== For the ''Non-Stock'' lines on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] form, in the '''Account''' column, the system inserts the Expense account defined by the '''Use COGS / Expense Account From''' setting of the posting class specified on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_60_00|Posting Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=IN206000|IN206000]) form. If the ''Subaccounts'' feature is enabled in your system, the system also inserts the subaccount, which is composed as defined by the '''Combine COGS / Expense Sub From''' setting of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_60_00|Posting Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=IN206000|IN206000]) form, in the '''Sub.''' column of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] form. {br}
Accounts and subaccounts are used for processing ''Non-Stock'' lines as follows:[anchor|#ul_okt_f2w_nt] *When a purchase order is created, the item amount is recorded to the Expense account (with the Expense subaccount). *When a purchase receipt linked to the purchase order is released, the line amount is moved from the Expense account (with the Expense subaccount) to the PO Accrual account (with the PO Accrual subaccount). *When a bill is created for the receipt, the amount is moved back from the PO Accrual account (with the PO Accrual subaccount) to the Expense account (with the Expense subaccount).
The Expense and PO Accrual accounts to be used for receipt-related transactions are defined by the posting class of the item on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_60_00|Posting Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=IN206000|IN206000]) form; the default accounts assigned to the item on the '''GL Accounts''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] form will be used if the posting class's '''Use COGS / Expense Account From''' and '''Use PO Accrual Account From''' settings have the ''Inventory Item'' option selected. The Expense subaccount and PO Accrual subaccount are also defined by the settings of posting class of the item; the default subaccounts assigned to the item on the''' GL Accounts''' tab will be used as the segment value sources for the resulting subaccounts based on the '''Combine COGS / Expense Sub From''' and '''Combine PO Accrual Sub From''' rules. For more information, see [HelpRoot_InvMgmt\IN__con_Posting_Classes__Definition_and_Usage|Posting Classes in Inventory]. ==Rules for Closing and Completing Non-Stock Lines== The way the lines of the ''Non-Stock'' type are completed and closed depends on the completion rule specified for the applicable non-stock item in the '''Complete PO Line''' box on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202000|IN202000]) form. The system determines if a line of the ''Non-Stock'' type should be closed and completed by using the following rules: [anchor|#_857f97f2-07ea-4acf-b261-d816eb8ea88a] *If ''By Quantity'' is selected in the '''Complete PO Line''' box for the item (the default option for non-stock items of the ''Non-Stock Item'' type), the purchase order line is considered completed in either of the following cases: **If the sum of the received quantity for the released purchase receipts prepared for the line is equal to or greater than the quantity of the purchase order line &#42; ('''Complete On %'''/100) **On release of the purchase receipt prepared for the line if the user has selected the '''Completed''' check box manually *:With the ''By Quantity'' completion rule selected for the item, the line is considered closed on release of the purchase receipt or AP bill if the sum of the received quantity for all released purchase receipts prepared for this line is equal to the line quantity in all released AP bills prepared for this line, and the quantity in the AP bill lines is equal to or greater than purchase order line quantity &#42; ('''Complete On %'''/100). The line is also considered closed on release of the purchase receipt or AP bill if the sum of the received quantity for all released purchase receipts prepared for this line is equal to the line quantity in all released AP bills prepared for this line, and the user has selected the '''Completed''' check box manually in the purchase receipt line. *If ''By Amount'' is selected in the '''Complete PO Line''' box for the item (the default option for non-stock items of the ''Labor, Service, Charge'', and ''Expense'' types), the purchase order line is considered completed in either of the following cases: **Automatically if the system has closed the line (that is, if the '''Closed''' check box is selected) **On release of the purchase receipt prepared for the line if the user has selected the '''Completed''' check box manually *:With the ''By Quantity'' completion rule selected for the item, the line is considered closed on release of the purchase receipt or AP bill if the sum of received quantity for all released purchase receipts prepared for this line is equal to the quantity in all released AP bills prepared for this line, and if the amount in the AP bill lines is equal to or greater than the amount of the purchase order line.
If a user processes the lines of a purchase order partially, multiple related purchase receipts and AP bills can be prepared for a single purchase order. The system determines which purchase order lines should be added to the prepared purchase receipt or AP bill depending on the status of the '''Completed''' and '''Closed''' check boxes in each line, as follows:[anchor|#_754bdfa6-cfdc-49aa-b7a9-0552abda029e] *Completed purchase order lines are not added to the purchase receipt. *Closed lines are added to neither purchase receipts nor AP bills.
If all purchase order lines have the '''Completed''' check box selected, and at least one line still has the '''Closed''' check box cleared, the purchase order is assigned the ''Completed'' status. If all purchase order lines have the '''Completed''' and '''Closed''' check boxes selected, the purchase order is assigned the ''Closed'' status. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Purchase_of_Stock|Stock Item Lines in Purchase Orders] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Purchase_of_Services|Service Lines in Purchase Orders]

For each non-stock item, you define whether a purchase receipt is required by selecting or clearing the '''Require Receipt''' check box on the '''General Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202000|IN202000]) form. In a purchase order line on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form, when you select a non-stock item that does not require receipt, the system inserts ''Service'' as the line type; also, the system inserts the ''Service'' line type in purchase order lines with no item specified. Although the ''Service'' lines are not tracked in inventory and do not require receipt, if you want to list them in purchase receipts for informational purposes, you can configure the system so that these lines are added to purchase receipts.{br}
This topic describes how the system processes ''Service'' lines added to a purchase order, and explains how the lines with these items are completed.{br}{TOC}[anchor|#servlines] ==General Workflow and Related Documents== The following diagram illustrates how the ''Service'' lines in purchase orders can be processed depending on the system settings.[anchor|#_5cbad372-ea71-49f0-a976-51e36baa1a61][anchor|#_72644f85-0573-4629-96c9-891ba85ab88d][image:UserGuide/Images/PO_Service_Lines.png|popup|450px] The remainder of this topic describes in detail the processing steps shown in the diagram and issues related to how this processing unfolds. The processing of the service order consists of the following steps:[anchor|#_8d7c5a90-a14c-4ed8-abd9-78251d245624] #''Entering a purchase order'' #:You enter a purchase order of the ''Normal'' type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form, and you add a ''Service'' line or multiple lines to the order. The reference number for a new purchase order is generated in accordance with the numbering sequence specified on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_10_10_00|Purchase Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=PO101000|PO101000]) form. If the order is created with the ''On Hold'' status, you should clear the '''Hold''' check box for the order to process it further. For details about the settings specified in the purchase order, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Purchase_Order_Processing|Purchase Order Creation]. #''Conditionally processing ''Service'' lines'' #:The way the system processes ''Service'' lines depends on the state of the '''Process Service Lines from Normal Purchase Orders via Purchase Receipt''' check box on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_10_10_00|Purchase Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=PO101000|PO101000]) form. #:If the check box is cleared (the default setting), processing ''Service'' lines doesn&rsquo;t involve creating a purchase receipt; an AP bill (or multiple bills) has to be created directly from the purchase order (see Step 4). When a user creates a purchase receipt for a purchase order with lines of different types, some of which require receipt and some of which do not require receipt, the system does not copy ''Service'' lines to a purchase receipt that is prepared from this purchase order. Also, in this case, ''Service'' lines cannot be added to the purchase receipt manually. #''Preparing a purchase receipt (optional)'' #: If the '''Process Service Lines from Normal Purchase Orders via Purchase Receipt''' check box is selected, a purchase receipt is required for the lines of the ''Service'' type. A user creates a purchase receipt from a purchase order by clicking '''Actions &gt; Enter PO Receipt''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] form. The prepared purchase receipt is available for reviewing on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form. If the purchase receipt is created with the ''On Hold'' status, you should clear the '''Hold''' check box for the receipt to process it further. #:As an alternative to creating the purchase receipt while viewing the purchase order, a user can create a new purchase receipt manually and add ''Service'' lines to it by clicking '''Add PO''' or '''Add PO Line''' on the table toolbar of the '''Document Details''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] form and using the dialog box that opens. #''Preparing an AP bill'' #:You prepare the AP bill by clicking '''Actions &gt; Enter AP Bill''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] form. The system brings up the generated AP bill on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP301000|AP301000]) form.
==Processing of the Accounts Payable Bill for the Purchase Order== The general workflow of processing purchase orders with lines of any type is to process a purchase receipt (if it is needed) before creating an AP bill (see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_scn_Purchase_with_Receipt|Purchase with Receipt Before Billing] for details). However, if you receive bills from a particular vendor before the ordered items are received to inventory, you can configure this vendor so that for the purchase orders of this vendor, you can create and process an AP bill before the purchase receipt is released. {br}
To do this, you need to select the '''Allow AP Bill Before Receipt''' check box in the vendor settings on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_30_00|Vendors] ([~/?ScreenId=AP303000|AP303000]) form; in addition, you can select this check box for a particular vendor location on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_30_10|Vendor Locations] ([~/?ScreenId=AP303010|AP303010]) form. The state of this check box is copied to each purchase order created for this vendor, and can be reviewed on the '''Other Information''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form. For a detailed description on how to process a purchase order with the associated bill being prepared before the receipt, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_scn_Purchase_with_Bill_Before_Receipt|Purchase with Billing Before Receipt]. ==Posting Accounts for Service Lines== When you add a ''Service'' line to a purchase order on the '''Document Details''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form, in the '''Account''' column, the system inserts the expense account defined by the '''Use COGS / Expense Account''' setting of the posting class on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_60_00|Posting Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=IN206000|IN206000]) form. If the'' Subaccounts'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, in the '''Sub.''' column of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] form, the system inserts the subaccount composed as defined by the '''Combine COGS / Expense Sub From''' setting of the posting class on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_60_00|Posting Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=IN206000|IN206000]) form. ==Rules for Closing and Completing Service Lines== The way the lines of the ''Service'' type (including the ''Service'' lines with the '''Inventory ID''' column empty) are completed and closed depends on whether the service lines are processed through receipts, and on the completion rule specified for each non-stock item in the '''Complete PO Line''' box on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202000|IN202000]) form. ((({S:Hint}If you change the '''Complete PO Line''' setting for a non-stock item on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] form, the system does not change this setting for already existing purchase orders; the newly specified setting applies to new purchase orders only. Existing purchase orders will be billed with the settings that were specified when the order was entered. ))) The system determines if a line of the ''Service'' type should be closed and completed by using the following rules: [anchor|#_88f1e6e2-f406-4a14-8465-5748e51cfe98] *If the ''Service'' line is processed through a receipt and ''By Amount'' is selected in the '''Complete PO Line''' box for an item, the line is completed automatically when the line is closed or on release of the purchase receipt if the user has selected the '''Completed''' check box manually. The line is closed in either of the following cases: **When a purchase receipt for the line is released if a user has selected the '''Complete PO Line''' check box manually in the purchase receipt line on the '''Document Details''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form. **When an AP bill for the line is released if the billed quantity for all bills that have been released for this line is equal to or greater than the amount of the purchase order line. *If the ''Service'' line is processed through a receipt and ''By Quantity'' is selected in the '''Complete PO Line''' box for an item, the line is closed when an AP bill for the line is released if the sum of the line quantities in all released bills for this line is equal to or greater than the quantity of the purchase order line &#42; ('''Complete On %'''/100). The line is completed in the following cases: **Automatically if the system has closed the line (that is, if the '''Closed''' check box is selected) **On release of the purchase receipt prepared for the line if the user has selected the '''Completed''' check box manually **If the sum of the received quantity for the released purchase receipts prepared for the line is equal to or greater than the quantity of the purchase order line &#42; ('''Complete On %'''/100) *If the ''Service'' line is processed without a receipt and ''By Amount'' is selected in the '''Complete PO Line''' box for the line item, the line is closed on release of the AP bill if the billed amount for all released bills for this line is equal to or greater than the amount of the purchase order line. The line is completed automatically when it is closed. *If the ''Service'' line is processed without a receipt and ''By Quantity'' is selected in the '''Complete PO Line''' box for the line item, the line is closed on release of the AP bill if the sum of the quantities in released bills for this line is equal to or greater than the quantity of the purchase order line &#42; ('''Complete On %'''/100). The line is completed automatically when it is closed.
If a user processes the lines of a purchase order partially, multiple related purchase receipts and AP bills can be prepared for a single purchase order. The system determines which purchase order lines should be added to the prepared purchase receipt or AP bill depending on the status of the '''Completed''' and '''Closed''' check boxes in each line, as follows:[anchor|#_7aed7b2c-e176-4580-9d67-86bb979340fb] *Completed purchase order lines are not added to the purchase receipt. *Closed lines are added to neither purchase receipts nor AP bills.
If all purchase order lines have the '''Completed''' check box selected, and at least one line still has the '''Closed''' check box cleared, the purchase order is assigned the ''Completed'' status. If all purchase order lines have the '''Completed''' and '''Closed''' check boxes selected, the purchase order is assigned the ''Closed'' status. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Purchase_of_NStock_w_Receipt|Non-Stock Lines in Purchase Orders] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Purchase_of_Stock|Stock Item Lines in Purchase Orders]

A purchase receipt is used to track the one-time receipt of goods purchased from a single vendor. The purchase receipt can be linked to a purchase order (or to multiple orders) to verify purchase order fulfillment, or the purchase receipt can be processed independently without being linked to any purchase orders. {br}

This topic describes the possible ways you can create purchase receipts. For the general workflow of processing purchase receipts in Acumatica ERP, see the topics of the [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Purchase_Order_Processing|Purchase Order Creation] section. {br}{TOC}
==Creating a Purchase Receipt Based on a Purchase Order==
If purchase orders are involved in your purchasing workflow, you can create a purchase receipt for the goods or services received for this particular purchase order by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Enter PO Receipt''' on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form. The system opens the created purchase receipt on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form, where you can review it.{br}

The lines that appear in a purchase receipt based on a purchase order depend on the line type of each line and on particular system settings that affect line processing. For more details on different types of lines added to purchase receipts, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_LineTypes|Line Types in Purchase Orders]. For a detailed description on processing a purchase order and all related documents, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Purchase_Order_Processing|Purchase Order Creation].{br}

For each purchase order or purchase order line added to the purchase receipt, the system calculates the quantities of the received goods, and displays this value for each line in the '''Qty. On Receipts''' column on the '''Document Details''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form. If all purchase order lines have been received in full, and if at least one line has not yet been billed in full, the purchase order is assigned the ''Completed'' status.((({S:Hint}For blanket purchase orders, the quantities of items in the '''Qty. On Receipts''' column are updated from the lines of the normal purchase orders linked to these blanket orders. 
)))
==Creating a Direct Purchase Receipt==
You can create a direct purchase receipt and process it without linking it to any purchase order. When goods are received, you create a new purchase receipt document on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form. On the '''Document Details''' tab, you add lines to specify the quantity and additional details of all received goods.{br}

 If lot or serial numbers are tracked for the received items, they may be assigned at the time of receipt if they are configured to do so. To view the assigned lot and serial numbers of the received items, click '''Allocations''' on the table toolbar of the '''Document Details''' tab. You can allocate stock items that have the ''Goods for IN'' line type, and lot- or serial-tracked stock items that have the ''Goods for Drop-Ship'' line type and that belong to the lot/serial class for which the '''Required for Drop Shipments''' check box is selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_70_00|Lot/Serial Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=IN207000|IN207000]) form.{br}

For detailed instructions on creating and processing a direct purchase receipt, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_scn_Direct_Purchase_Receipt|Purchase with Direct Purchase Receipt].
==Linking Purchase Orders or Their Lines to an Existing Purchase Receipt==
When you receive purchases from a single vendor and create a new purchase receipt on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form, you can add an entire purchase order, multiple purchase orders, or particular purchase order lines to this receipt. The lines that can be added to a purchase receipt depend on the line types of these lines and on particular system settings. For more information about which lines are processed through purchase receipts, see the topics of the [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_LineTypes|Line Types in Purchase Orders] part.{br}

Purchase receipts can be linked to only normal or drop-ship purchase orders; see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Types_of_Purchase_Orders|Types of Purchase Orders] for details about these and other purchase order types. 
==Consolidating Multiple Purchase Orders into a Single Purchase Receipt==
For a new purchase receipt that you have created by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form, you can add multiple purchase orders of the same vendor. You can add an entire purchase order or individual purchase order lines. The lines that can be added to a purchase receipt depend on the line types of these lines and on particular system settings. For more information about which lines are processed through purchase receipts, see the topics of the [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_LineTypes|Line Types in Purchase Orders] part.{br}

Purchase receipts can be linked to only normal or drop-ship purchase orders; see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_Types_of_Purchase_Orders|Types of Purchase Orders] for details about these and other purchase order types. 
==Assigning Purchase Receipts for Processing==
You may need to distribute receipts among employees for processing. To enable automatic assignment of receipts based on the receipt properties, you can create an assignment map by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_55_00|Assignment and Approval Maps] ([~/?ScreenId=EP205500|EP205500]) form and specify the map in the '''Receipt Assignment Map''' box on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_10_10_00|Purchase Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=PO101000|PO101000]) form. Then when a new receipt is created, it will be automatically assigned to the appropriate employee for processing.
==Related Articles==
