==Notes About the Procedure==[anchor|#_95e59d95-cd52-4f18-a43b-2412e2479aee] The notes in this section describe the nuances of the UI elements available on the form, such as when an element is required and when it is not, and when the system fills in settings by default. This section can include other notes.{br}
Note the following about adding landed costs to a bill:[anchor|#ul_lqk_24v_tz] *You can link a landed costs line to a line with empty '''Inventory ID''' only. Once you have linked a landed cost line, the description of a bill line changes to the description of the linked landed cost. *Each bill line can be linked to only one landed cost line. *The '''Link Line''' dialog box shows the lines of released landed cost documents for which the Accounts Payable bill wasn&rsquo;t created on release. *If the amount in the bill line differs from the amount in the landed cost line that you linked, the occurred difference is posted to the Landed Cost Variance account. For details, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\PO__con_LC_Postponed|Adjusting the Landed Cost Variance].

The Purchase Requisitions module, a part of the inventory and order management functionality, provides your organization with ability to create and process requests for goods and services, approve requests, and prevent cost overruns. The Purchase Requisitions module provides configurable, budget-compliant request documents. Also, the module facilitates a bidding process.{br}
The purchase requisitions functionality is available only if the ''Purchase Requisitions'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. If available, this module is integrated with the financial modules, as well as with the Inventory and Purchase Orders modules.{br}
This chapter contains information you need to configure and use the purchase requisitions functionality. ==In This Chapter==[anchor|#table_zth_1z3_chb] {| class="checklist invisiblechecklist" | width="100%" |- | [anchor|#ul_ixn_1z3_chb] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\RQ__con_Basic_Requisitions|Basic Purchase Requisition Process] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\RQ__con_Extended_Requisitions|Extended Purchase Requisition Process] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\RQ__con_Bidding_Process|Processing and Selection of Bids]
| |}

An organization may want to pursue a clear, cost-efficient purchasing process that prioritizes the purchase of items from the most appropriate vendors at the best possible time and in the right quantities. To facilitate this process, an organization can use purchase requests and requisitions—that is, documents that track the items the organization wants to purchase from vendors. In Acumatica ERP, you can create requests, create purchase requisitions based on these requests, and solicit bids from multiple vendors so that your personnel can select the best bid.{br}
To use the requisition functionality, you must have the ''Purchase Requisitions'' feature enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form.{br}
In this topic, you will find information about the basic process of purchase requisitions in Acumatica ERP.{br}{TOC} ==Request Classes in Acumatica ERP== A request class is an entity in Acumatica ERP that contains the general settings for requests of a particular type. You can create a request class on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_20_10_00|Request Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ201000|RQ201000]) form and specify the following settings for the class:[anchor|#ul_vf2_yhl_wfb] *What the promised lead time is: In the '''Promised Lead Time (days)''' box (Summary area), you specify the number of days within which a request of the class should be fulfilled. *Whether requests of the class are external or internal: External requests contain items requested by customers of your organization. To indicate that the request class will be used for external requests, you select the '''Customer Request''' check box in the Summary area. Internal requests are initiated by employees of your organization and contain items that the employees need in their work. *Whether the items from a request of the class can be divided among multiple vendors: If a request contains multiple items, you can order these items from multiple vendors if one vendor cannot fulfill the entire request or if another vendor has lower prices for particular items. You select the '''Allow Multiple Vendors per Request''' check box, also in the Summary area, to indicate that the system can suggest multiple vendors to fulfill the request. *Which items are available for ordering in requests of this class (optional): You can restrict the list of items that users can add to the request during creation to reduce the probability of mistakenly added items. To do this, you select the '''Restrict Requests Items to the Specified List''' check box in the Summary area, and you add the items to the list on the '''Request Class Item List''' tab. *Whether the request must be validated against the budget: If you control expenses on particular items by using budgets, you can set up budget validation on the '''GL Accounts''' tab by selecting ''Warning'' or ''Error'' in the '''Budget Validation''' box (the default setting is ''None'') and specifying an expense account in the '''Expense Account''' box (and the corresponding subaccount, if applicable, in the '''Expense Sub. '''box).
==Purchase Requisition Usage== In a simple case of using purchase requests and requisitions, you create one request or multiple requests, and then you create a purchase requisition based on the requests, manually select a vendor, and purchase items from this vendor (see the following diagram). You can use this simplified process, for example, when employees of your organization order low-cost items, such as office supplies. If you already work with a vendor that gives your company the best prices and discounts for these items, you do not need to gather bids from multiple vendors to save on price.[anchor|#fig_cv1_nq3_chb][anchor|#image_dv1_nq3_chb][image:UserGuide/Images/Requisition_Internal.png|popup|Overview of the simplified requisition process|450px] If your organization works with multiple vendors that provide you with the same type of items (such as computers), you can request and process vendor bids to select the best offers. For example, if you have received an order for laptops from your employees, you can find a vendor or multiple vendors with the lowest prices to fulfill the order.{br}
Depending on the business processes of your organization, you can use budget validation for requests or approvals for requests and requisitions to secure the purchase requisitions process against fraud and unnecessary expenses. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\RQ__con_Extended_Requisitions|Extended Purchase Requisition Process]. ==Basic Purchase Requisition Process== The basic purchase requisition process includes the following steps (also shown in the diagrams below):[anchor|#ol_v1c_wfk_wfb] #Creating a request: You create a request by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_10_00|Requests] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ301000|RQ301000]) form. #Creating a purchase requisition based on one request or multiple requests: You create a purchase requisition on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_50_40_00|Create Requisitions] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ504000|RQ504000]) form. #Sending proposals to vendors by email (optional): You automatically send requests for proposals to vendors by email by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_20_00|Requisitions] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ302000|RQ302000]) form. #Selecting a vendor (or multiple vendors) for the purchase: #*If you manually select a vendor (or multiple vendors for different items) for the requisition, you use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_20_00|Requisitions] form. #*If you have run automatic bidding, you analyze and correct the automatic bidding results by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_50_30_00|Complete Bidding] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ503000|RQ503000]) form. #:For details on selecting vendors, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\RQ__con_Bidding_Process|Processing and Selection of Bids]. #Creating all needed purchase orders (and, optionally, all needed sales orders for external requests): You create these orders by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_20_00|Requisitions] form. #Sending all purchase orders that have been created to the applicable vendors: By using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form, you send the created purchase order or orders to the vendor or vendors selected to fulfill the requisition. #Receiving items in a warehouse: You create and process the documents related to the items being received in a warehouse by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] and [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) forms. #Providing items to requesters: For external requests, you use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) and [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302000|SO302000]) forms to create and process the documents for shipping items to customers. For internal requests, you can create and process the documents for issuing items to employees of your organization by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_20_00|Issues] ([~/?ScreenId=IN302000|IN302000]) form. [anchor|#fig_mxv_jr3_chb][anchor|#image_nxv_jr3_chb][image:UserGuide/Images/Requisition_for_Customers_Part1.png|popup|Overview of requisition process with bids (part 1)|450px][anchor|#fig_f3p_lr3_chb][anchor|#image_g3p_lr3_chb][image:UserGuide/Images/Requisition_for_Customers_Part2.png|popup|Overview of requisition process with bids (part 2)|450px] ==Creation of a Purchase Requisition Document== After the requests have been created, you create a requisition document. You can include multiple requests in one requisition if the items in these requests will be ordered from the same vendors. For creating a requisition, you can use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_50_40_00|Create Requisitions] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ504000|RQ504000]) or [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_20_00|Requisitions] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ302000|RQ302000]) form. On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_50_40_00|Create Requisitions] form, you can create any number of requisitions. While on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_20_00|Requisitions] form, you can fully process a requisition (from creation to release).{br}
When the system is creating a requisition, it can merge lines with the same items into one line if the item was requested by the same requester (a customer or an employee) and has the same estimated unit cost. If you want the system to merge items in all requisitions, you can select the '''Merge Lines by Default''' check box on the '''General Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_10_10_00|Purchase Requisitions Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ101000|RQ101000]) form. Before you create any requisitions on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_50_40_00|Create Requisitions] form, you can select the '''Merge Lines''' check box in the Selection area to merge items for created requisitions, or clear the check box to not merge items.{br}
If a requisition has already been created, you can merge lines manually on the '''Document Details''' tab of the Requisitions form by selecting the Included check box for the lines in the list and clicking '''Merge Lines''' on the table toolbar.((({S:Hint}With manual merging in this way, the system will merge lines even if they have different unit costs and requesters. For external requests, we do not recommend that you merge items requested by different customers, because this may cause sales documents to be linked incorrectly to purchase requisitions. ))) ==Sending of Requests for Proposals== If you have email functionality configured in the system, you can automatically send requests for proposals to vendors by email by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_20_00|Requisitions] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ302000|RQ302000]) form. To do this, on the '''Bidding''' tab, you select a vendor in the '''Bidding Vendors''' table and click '''Send Request'''. Alternatively, you can send requests to all vendors at once by clicking '''Vendor Notifications''' > '''Send All Requests''' on the form toolbar. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\RQ__con_Bidding_Process|Processing and Selection of Bids] *[HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_20_10_00|Request Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ201000|RQ201000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_10_00|Requests] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ301000|RQ301000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_20_00|Requisitions] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ302000|RQ302000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_50_40_00|Create Requisitions] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ504000|RQ504000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_50_50_00|Create Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ505000|RQ505000])

If your organization takes measures to secure the purchasing process against fraud and unnecessary expenses, in Acumatica ERP, you can configure validation of requests against budget and approval of requests and requisitions as extensions of the basic process.{br}
In this topic, you will read about the extended process of purchase requisitions.{br}{TOC} ==Advanced Purchase Requisition Process== The purchasing process that involves budget validation and approval of requests and requisitions includes the following steps (also shown in the diagrams below):[anchor|#ol_v1c_wfk_wfb] #Creating a request: You create a request by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_10_00|Requests] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ301000|RQ301000]) form. #Validating a request against a budget: You analyze the validation results on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_10_00|Requests] form and correct the list of items if the request cost exceeds the budget. #Approving the request: The employee that is assigned as the request approver approves or rejects the request by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_50_30_10|Approvals] ([~/?ScreenId=EP503010|EP503010]) or [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_10_00|Requests] form. #Creating a purchase requisition based on one request or multiple requests: You create a purchase requisition on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_50_40_00|Create Requisitions] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ504000|RQ504000]) form. #Approving the requisition: The assigned requisition approver approves or rejects the requisition by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_50_30_10|Approvals] or [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_10_00|Requests] form. #Sending notifications to vendors: On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_20_00|Requisitions] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ302000|RQ302000]) form, you send a request for proposal to each vendor that may opt to participate in bidding by clicking the vendor on the '''Bidding''' tab (in the '''Bidding Vendors''' table) and clicking '''Send Request''' on the table toolbar. #Entering vendor responses: You enter vendor responses into the system by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_30_00|Bidding Responses] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ303000|RQ303000]) form. #Running automatic bidding: On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_50_30_00|Complete Bidding] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ503000|RQ503000]) form, you run automatic bidding among vendors. #Selecting a vendor (or multiple vendors) for the purchase: You use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_20_00|Requisitions] form to manually select a vendor (or multiple vendors for different items) for the requisition. If you have run automatic bidding, you analyze and correct the automatic bidding results by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_50_30_00|Complete Bidding] form. #Creating all needed purchase orders (and, optionally, all needed sales orders for external requests): You create these orders from the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_20_00|Requisitions] form. #Sending all purchase orders that have been created to the applicable vendors: By using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form, you send the created purchase order or orders to the vendor or vendors selected to fulfill the requisition. #Receiving items in a warehouse: You create and process the documents related to the items being received in a warehouse by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] and [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) forms. #Providing items to requesters: For external requests, you use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) and [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302000|SO302000]) forms to create and process the documents for shipping items to customers. For internal requests, you create and process the documents for issuing items to employees of your organization by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_20_00|Issues] ([~/?ScreenId=IN302000|IN302000]) form. [anchor|#fig_ktt_4w3_chb][anchor|#image_ltt_4w3_chb][image:UserGuide/Images/Requisition_Internal_Approval_Part1.png|popup|Process of purchase requisitions with budget validation and approval (part 1)|450px] [anchor|#fig_hxt_rw3_chb][anchor|#image_ixt_rw3_chb][image:UserGuide/Images/Requisition_Internal_Approval_Part2.png|popup|Process of purchase requisitions with budget validation and approval (part 2)|450px] ==Request and Requisition Approvals== In the system, you can create approval maps so that requests that meet particular criteria are submitted for approval to the appropriate employees. For example, if the total cost of the items in a request exceeds a particular amount, the request must be approved by the head of the department whose employee requested the items.{br}
You can configure the system so that particular requisitions or all requisitions require approval. For example, approval can be set up so that all requisitions that contain computer equipment that costs more than a particular amount must be approved by the IT department before purchasing can take place.{br}
Before you turn on the approval of requests and requisitions, you should make sure that the needed approval maps and notification templates (if needed) have been configured. The approval map defines the employees designated for approving documents and the conditions that the documents must meet (if applicable) to be assigned for approval; the template of the notification email will be used by the system for notifying approvers about the documents pending their approval.{br}
You then enable the approval of purchase requests or requisitions on the '''General Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_10_10_00|Purchase Requisitions Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ101000|RQ101000]) form by selecting the appropriate '''Require Approval''' check box (in the '''Request Settings''' or '''Requisition Settings''' section). Then on the '''Approval''' tab of this form, for each document type (request or requisition), you specify the approval map and, optionally, the template of the notification email. For the step-by-step instruction, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\RQ__how_Set_Up_Approval|To Set Up Approval of Requests and Requisitions].{br}
With approvals turned on, when a purchase request or requisition that is subject to approval has been created, taken off hold, and saved, the document is assigned the ''Pending Approval'' status. The responsible approver receives an email notification (if an email notification template has been specified for this type of document) about the document pending approval. On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_50_30_10|Approvals] ([~/?ScreenId=EP503010|EP503010]) form, an approver can review the list of documents pending approval, and can select one record or multiple records in the list and approve or reject all selected records.((({S:Hint}To be able to approve requests and requisitions, an approver must have access to the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_10_00|Requests] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ301000|RQ301000]) and [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_20_00|Requisitions] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ302000|RQ302000]) forms accordingly. ))) If the document is approved, the system assigns it the ''Open'' status, and document processing can continue.{br}
If the document is rejected, it is assigned the ''Rejected'' status, and you cannot continue processing the document. You can edit the document after you select the '''Hold''' check box on the corresponding form. ==Budget Validation for Requests== If your organization allocates budgets for valuable internal purchases, you can configure budget validation for requests to prevent cost overruns of requested goods and services. An employee who is creating a request can see whether the cost of the items included in the request is below the budget. If the cost exceeds the budget, the employee can edit the list of items in the request.{br}
Before you set up this validation, you should make sure that the budgets have been created and released in the system on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\GL_30_20_10|Budgets] ([~/?ScreenId=GL302010|GL302010]) form.{br}
The setup of budget validation for requests includes the following tasks:[anchor|#ol_znk_vdl_wfb] #Defining the way the system will calculate the costs of items included in a request: On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_10_10_00|Purchase Requisitions Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ101000|RQ101000]) form, in the '''Budget Ledger''' box of the '''General Settings''' tab, you select the budget ledger that the system will use for verification. You can also specify the time period over which the system will aggregate amounts from all requests created. In the '''Budget Calculation''' box, you select one of the following options: #*''YTD Values'': Calculates the total cost of requests created from the beginning of the financial year to the end of the current financial period #*''PTD Values'': Calculates the total cost of requests created from the beginning of the financial period #*''Annual'': Calculates the total cost of requests created for the current calendar year #Turning on budget validation in the settings of each needed request class: On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_20_10_00|Request Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ201000|RQ201000]) form, you turn on budget validation by selecting the appropriate option in the '''Budget Validation''' box of the '''GL Accounts''' tab. (The default setting is ''None''.) If you select ''Warning'', a user will be able to save a request of this class even if the requested amount exceeds the budgeted amount, but the system will display a warning. If you select ''Error'', a user will not be able to save a request of this class with an amount that exceeds the budgeted amount, and the system will display an error message.
==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\RQ__con_Basic_Requisitions|Basic Purchase Requisition Process] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\RQ__con_Bidding_Process|Processing and Selection of Bids] *[HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_50_30_10|Approvals] ([~/?ScreenId=EP503010|EP503010]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_20_10_00|Request Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ201000|RQ201000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_10_00|Requests] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ301000|RQ301000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_20_00|Requisitions] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ302000|RQ302000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_30_00|Bidding Responses] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ303000|RQ303000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_50_30_00|Complete Bidding] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ503000|RQ503000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_50_40_00|Create Requisitions] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ504000|RQ504000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_50_50_00|Create Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ505000|RQ505000])

The bidding process entails sending requests for proposals to vendors and choosing the vendor that best meets your company&rsquo;s needs. The Purchase Requisitions module of Acumatica ERP supports and streamlines the bidding process, helping you to reduce purchase expenses. You can manually assign a vendor to the requisition or select the vendor as a result of the bidding process.{br}
In this topic, you will read about how to process and select bids.{br}{TOC} ==Bid Processing== You begin the processing of vendors&rsquo; bids for a particular requisition when you receive responses (that is, bids) from vendors. The processing involves the following steps:[anchor|#ol_apb_pd3_chb] #You enter responses into the system by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_30_00|Bidding Responses] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ303000|RQ303000]) form. #You select the best bids in any of the following ways: #*By using the automatic algorithm of selecting the best bids. This algorithm uses information about vendor&rsquo;s prices, minimal quantities, and bid quantities of the requested items. For more details, see [[#section_yr3_5c3_chb|Automatic Selection of Bids]. #*By analyzing responses and selecting vendors manually. For details, see [[#section_hrq_5c3_chb|Manual Selection of Bids]. [anchor|#section_yr3_5c3_chb] ==Automatic Selection of Bids== You process the bids for a particular requisition by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_50_30_00|Complete Bidding] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ503000|RQ503000]) form. To run automatic bidding, you click '''Update Result''' on the form toolbar. The system selects a vendor or multiple vendors for each item automatically based on the offered price (bid unit cost) and the quantity limitations (bid quantity), if any, from vendor responses. You can view bidding results and correct them if you are not satisfied with the automatically selected vendors.{br}
If any vendor response has changed or been withdrawn after the system selected vendors for a requisition, you enter new responses on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_30_00|Bidding Responses] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ303000|RQ303000]) form. Then you go back to the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_50_30_00|Complete Bidding] form, click '''Clear Result''' on the form toolbar to clear the selected vendors for all lines of a requisition, and click '''Update Result''' again.{br}
After you have analyzed and corrected the bidding results, you accept the results by clicking '''Complete Bidding''' on the toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_50_30_00|Complete Bidding] form. The system assigns the selected vendor or vendors to the requisition.[anchor|#section_hrq_5c3_chb] ==Manual Selection of Bids== When selecting the best bids, you may want to analyze the bidding responses and select the bids manually. You may want to take into account not only the vendor offering the lowest price but also any of the following:[anchor|#ul_krq_5c3_chb] *The number of days needed to deliver the order *The carrier used by a vendor *The shipping terms used by a vendor *Special offers from a vendor
You can select a vendor with a better bid by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_20_00|Requisitions] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ302000|RQ302000]) form as follows: You click the vendor line in the '''Bidding Vendors''' table on the '''Bidding''' tab and click '''Choose Vendor''' on the table toolbar. ==User Roles for Bid Processing== To avoid fraud in selecting bids, you can control which employees can view bidding responses and results. If you want particular users to only enter bidding results, you create a user role that has access to the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_30_00|Bidding Responses] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ303000|RQ303000]) form and does not have access to the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_50_30_00|Complete Bidding] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ503000|RQ503000]) and [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_20_00|Requisitions] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ302000|RQ302000]) forms and assign this role to the users. For users who are selecting the best bids you create a user role with access to the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_50_30_00|Complete Bidding] and [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_20_00|Requisitions] forms and without access to the [HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_30_00|Bidding Responses] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ303000|RQ303000]) form and assign this role to the users. For more information, see [HelpRoot_Administration\SM__con_Role_Configuration|Access Rights for Roles]. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_20_00|Requisitions] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ302000|RQ302000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_30_30_00|Bidding Responses] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ303000|RQ303000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\RQ_50_30_00|Complete Bidding] ([~/?ScreenId=RQ503000|RQ503000])

On Acumatica ERP forms designed to facilitate automated warehouse operations, you can perform warehouse operations in an automated mode by using barcode scanners or mobile devices with a scanning option. {br}
If the ''Automated Warehouse Operations'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, you can automate standard warehouse operations with inventory items, such as picking, packaging, receiving, putting away, transferring, and counting. Depending on the operation that you are currently performing, you can switch between working modes on the current form or navigate to another form by using special barcodes. You can also configure carts to be used for picking and putting away the items, to track item movements between the warehouse locations. You can quickly review information for particular items, carts, and warehouses by scanning a barcode.{br}
The topics of this chapter describes the workflows that you can configure, depending on the business requirements of your company, to support automated processing of shipping, receiving, and inventory operations. ==In This Chapter==[anchor|#_cfa994c3-d7e7-4248-8699-a21ef90c8357] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_WMS|Automation of Warehouse Operations] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_WMS_Commands_List|Working Modes and Supported Commands] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Automating_WMS_PickPackShip|Pick, Pack, and Ship Operations] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Automating_WMS_ReceivePutAway|Receive and Put Away Operations] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\IN__con_Automating_WMS_ScanAndCount|Scan and Count Operation] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\IN__con_Automating_WMS_Scan_and_Issue|Scan and Issue Operation] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\IN__con_Automating_WMS_Scan_and_Receive|Scan and Receive Operation] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\IN__con_Automating_WMS_Scan_and_Transfer|Scan and Transfer Operation] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_WMS_LotSerial|Warehouse Operations with Lot- and Serial-Tracked Items] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_WMS_CartTracking|Cart Tracking in Warehouse Operations]

Acumatica ERP provides a solution to automate basic warehouse operations, such as picking, packaging, receiving, putting away, transferring, and counting of items. This functionality and the related forms become available if the ''Automated Warehouse Operations'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form.{br}
In this topic, you will read about the automation of warehouse operations in Acumatica ERP.{br}{TOC} ==Supported Warehouse Operations== You can automate the following warehouse operations by using a barcode scanner or a mobile device with barcode scanning support:[anchor|#ul_wdj_x5j_ygb] *Picking the items for a particular shipment. For details, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Automating_WMS_PickPackShip|Pick, Pack, and Ship Operations]. *Packing the items to fulfill a particular shipment, as described in [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Automating_WMS_PickPackShip|Pick, Pack, and Ship Operations]. *Shipping items based on a shipment defined in the system. For details, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Automating_WMS_PickPackShip|Pick, Pack, and Ship Operations]. *Receiving items based on a purchase receipt defined in the system. (See [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Automating_WMS_ReceivePutAway|Receive and Put Away Operations].) *Putting away received items based on a purchase receipt. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Automating_WMS_ReceivePutAway|Receive and Put Away Operations]. *Issuing items from a warehouse. For details, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\IN__con_Automating_WMS_Scan_and_Issue|Scan and Issue Operation]. *Transferring items within a warehouse or between warehouses located in the same building, as described in [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\IN__con_Automating_WMS_Scan_and_Transfer|Scan and Transfer Operation]. *Receiving items in a warehouse. For details, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\IN__con_Automating_WMS_Scan_and_Receive|Scan and Receive Operation]. *Counting items within the physical inventory. For details, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\IN__con_Automating_WMS_ScanAndCount|Scan and Count Operation].
In the system, a working mode corresponds to each of these operations (for more information, see [[#section_fy2_pbm_zgb|Working and Service Modes]). You can configure the workflow for each group of operations, as described in [[#section_bqz_sbm_zgb|Workflow Configuration].[anchor|#section_fy2_pbm_zgb] ==Working and Service Modes== The forms you use for automated warehouse operations provide both ''working modes'' and ''service modes''. Working modes are modes that correspond to key operations users perform while using the form. Service modes are modes that correspond to secondary operations, such as removing document lines.{br}
Some forms that support the automation of warehouse operations, such as [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_20|Pick, Pack, and Ship] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302020|SO302020]), have multiple working modes. Each mode of a form, which corresponds to the operation you are currently performing, shows different content and supports a different set of actions. Other forms, such as [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_40_20|Scan and Transfer] ([~/?ScreenId=IN304020|IN304020]), have only one working mode, so that you can perform only a particular operation by using this form.{br}
While you are performing warehouse operations, you can change the working mode on the current form or navigate from the current form to another form by entering special commands (or by scanning special barcodes) starting with @. For example, if you scan or enter <tt>@pack</tt> in the '''Scan''' box (which is on all of the forms related to automated warehouse operations), the system navigates to the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_20|Pick, Pack, and Ship] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302020|SO302020]) in Pack mode. When you change the mode of a form, the system keeps the current document selected. For example, if you have entered the shipment number in Pick mode and have entered the command (or have scanned the barcode) to switch to Pack mode, the system automatically selects the current shipment.{br}
On each form related to automated warehouse operations, you can activate any of the following service modes:[anchor|#ul_w3x_t2f_zgb] *Quantity Editing: In this mode, you can change a quantity of an item in the selected line. You activate the mode by scanning the <tt>&#42;qty</tt> barcode or by clicking '''Set Qty''' on the form toolbar. This mode is available if the '''Use Default Quantity''' check box is cleared on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_10_10_00|Sales Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SO101000|SO101000]) and [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_10_10_00|Purchase Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=PO101000|PO101000]) forms and the '''Use Default Quantity in ...''' check boxes are cleared on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_10_10_00|Inventory Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=IN101000|IN101000]) form. *Remove: In this mode, you can remove the selected document line or a specific quantity of the inventory item from the current document. You activate the mode by scanning the <tt>&#42;remove</tt> barcode or by clicking '''Remove''' on the form toolbar. *Cart-specific modes: **Cart Loading: In this mode, you load the selected cart with items. When you start picking or putting away items by using a cart, the system activates this mode automatically. If you want to activate this mode after unloading a cart, you scan the <tt>&#42;cart&#42;in</tt> command while using the corresponding form. **Cart Unloading: In this mode, you unload the selected cart. You activate the mode by scanning the <tt>&#42;cart&#42;out</tt> command.
In addition to having multiple modes, each of the forms provided by the ''Automated Warehouse Operations'' feature has the '''Scan Log''' tab, which shows a log of the data scanned or entered in the '''Scan''' box. (Depending on preferences of the forms related to purchase orders and sales orders functionality, this tab can be hidden.)[anchor|#section_bqz_sbm_zgb] ==Workflow Configuration== You can configure the workflow for each group of related operations so that the workflow corresponds to the business processes of your organization. For example, when shipping items, you can use only the Pick, Pack, or Ship mode, use them in any combination, or use all the modes in the same workflow. When receiving items with a purchase order, you can use either the Receive mode or the Put Away mode, or you can use both modes in one workflow. Additionally, you can track the use of carts for picking and putting away items (for more details, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_WMS_CartTracking|Cart Tracking in Warehouse Operations]).{br}
For more information about workflow configuration and other settings, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_WMS_Config|Configuration of Warehouse Operation Workflows]. ==Special Commands for Scanning== When you work in any of the modes, you can use special commands to quickly switch to another mode or to perform an action in the current mode. You can scan a barcode of the command or type the command in the '''Scan''' box of a processing form. For the list of commands, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_WMS_Commands_List|Working Modes and Supported Commands]. ==Operations with Lot- and Serial-Tracked Items== If the ''Lot and Serial Tracking'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, while using the forms that facilitate the automated processing of warehouse operations, you can process items with lot or serial numbers in any mode. For details, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_WMS_LotSerial|Warehouse Operations with Lot- and Serial-Tracked Items]. ==Support of Automatic and Manual Packaging== If the ''Automatic Packaging'' feature is disabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form, while you are performing picking and packing operations on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_20|Pick, Pack, and Ship] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302020|SO302020]) form, you specify the packaging options for the order manually.{br}
If the ''Automatic Packaging'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form, when you process a shipment in Pick mode, all applicable boxes are selected and confirmed, and the box weight is specified automatically. If a single box was automatically specified for a shipment while you picked the items, then in Pack mode, the system automatically specifies the packaging details and confirms the box. Shipments for which multiple boxes were assigned cannot be packed automatically; you have to manually specify the packaging details and confirm the boxes. For a description of the picking and packing processes, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Automating_WMS_PickPackShip|Pick, Pack, and Ship Operations]. ==Search for Items== As you perform any of the warehouse operations, you may need to search for items. For example, you might find a box that is not in storage and want to get information about what is in the box, or you may need to view the full list of items in a specific location or cart.{br}
To get information about a particular item by scanning the item barcode, you can use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_25_20|Item Lookup] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202520|IN202520]) form.{br}
If you want to view the list of items in a specific location or a cart, you can scan the barcode of the location or cart when the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_40_90_20|Storage Lookup] ([~/?ScreenId=IN409020|IN409020]) form is opened on the screen of your device.{br}
You can switch to either of these forms in any of the working modes by scanning or typing the corresponding command. For the list of commands, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_WMS_Commands_List|Working Modes and Supported Commands]. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_WMS_CartTracking|Cart Tracking in Warehouse Operations] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_WMS_Config|Configuration of Warehouse Operation Workflows] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_WMS_LotSerial|Warehouse Operations with Lot- and Serial-Tracked Items] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_WMS_Commands_List|Working Modes and Supported Commands]

If the ''Fulfillment'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, you can perform automated picking, packing, and shipping operations with inventory items by using a barcode scanner or a mobile device with a scanning option. {br}
This topic describes the workflows of automated operations that you can configure in Acumatica ERP for processing shipments.{br}{TOC} ==Applicable Documents== You perform automated operations for processing shipments on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_20|Pick, Pack, and Ship] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302020|SO302020]) form. {br}
You can process the following documents in Pick mode:[anchor|#_bef6af98-4154-4241-adc5-0b93ad7bc68b] *Open shipments of the ''Shipment'' operation type (shipments prepared for sales orders) *Open shipments of the ''Transfer'' operation type (shipments prepared for transfer orders) *Open shipments of the ''Receipt'' operation type (shipments prepared for return orders)
In Pack mode, you can process open shipments of the ''Shipment'' or ''Transfer'' operation type. (If the picking of items is required before packing, the shipment must have at least one picked item.) ==Workflow Variations== Based on the settings specified on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_10_10_00|Sales Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SO101000|SO101000]) form, the following shipping workflow variations can be configured and used:[anchor|#_77cd0a10-0afb-41a2-823d-433d4616753b] *A user processes the picking of items in Pick mode, and then processes the packing of items in Pack mode. *In Pick mode, a user processes the picking of items and confirms the shipment. *In Pack mode, a user processes the packing of items (without first picking them) and confirms the shipment. *In Pick mode, a user processes the picking of items and enters a shipping location for each item. *In Pack mode, a user processes the packing of items, and the system automatically calculates weight of each package.
In addition, in any of these workflow variations, the user can switch to Ship mode (see [[#_6419ca4e-632c-419d-aa23-d600eff07fa6|Workflow of Automated Shipping]) before confirming the shipment, and select shipping options, such as the particular carrier and carrier rate to be used for shipping.{br}
For more information on configuring workflows, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_WMS_Config|Configuration of Warehouse Operation Workflows]. ==Workflow of Automated Picking== The automated processing of the picking of items to be packed involves the actions shown in the following diagram.[anchor|#_9a92ac48-c9f2-40e0-be74-8656e0577935][anchor|#_15a75575-9e06-4bd9-be65-29b6a9a63fd9][image:UserGuide/Images/WMS_Pick.png|popup|450px] To process the picking of items by using Pick mode, you perform the following steps:[anchor|#_fc3acd1f-81f8-43c4-af60-3107a80987dc] #''Switch to Pick mode''. #:You switch to Pick mode by scanning or entering the ''@pick'' barcode. The system opens the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_20|Pick, Pack, and Ship] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302020|SO302020]) form with the '''Pick''' tab displayed. #''Scan the document number''. #:To start automated processing, you scan the reference number of the shipment to be processed. The system displays the lines of the scanned document in the table and inserts the reference number of the document that is currently selected for processing in the '''Shipment Nbr.''' box. #''Scan the location barcode''. #:When you scan the barcode of the location from which the item is picked, the system searches for the location in the lines of the document that is currently selected. #''Scan the item barcode''. #:When you scan the item barcode of the picked item, the system searches for the item in the lines of the currently selected document. The system displays the picked quantity in the '''Picked Qty.''' column and highlights the line (with bold if the line has been picked partially, or in green if the line has been picked in full). If the barcode of the scanned item is specified for a non-base unit of measure (UOM), the system converts this quantity to the picked quantity in the base unit of measure for this item. #Optional: ''Scan the lot or serial number of the item''. #:This step is required only if the item is lot- or serial-tracked item, and only if the '''Default Auto-Generated Lot/Serial Nbr.''' check box is cleared on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_10_10_00|Sales Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SO101000|SO101000]) form. If the check box is selected, the system specifies the lot or serial number for the serialized item automatically. #Optional: ''Scan the item quantity''. #:To change the picked quantity in the line that is currently being processed, you switch to Quantity Editing mode by scanning or entering the <tt>&#42;qty</tt> barcode, and manually enter the quantity in the UOM of the scanned item barcode. #Optional: ''Scan the barcode to confirm the picked quantity''. #:If no more changes are needed for the line that is currently being processed, you scan the <tt>&#42;ok</tt> barcode or click the '''OK''' button to confirm the picked quantity. #''Pick another line''. #:If another item needs to be picked for the currently selected location, you scan the item barcode (return to Step 4), and repeat the process for the item. #''Pick items from another location''. #:If you need to pick items from another location, you scan the location barcode (return to Step 3), and repeat the process for the location. #''Complete the picking process''. #:If you have finished the picking operation and packaging is not needed, you scan the <tt>&#42;confirm&#42;shipment</tt> barcode or click the '''Confirm Shipment''' button on the form toolbar. The system confirms the shipment that is currently being processed. #:If you have finished the picking operation, to proceed with packaging, you scan the <tt>@pack</tt> barcode to switch to Pack mode. [anchor|#_8df7a03c-f6cf-4cb5-9375-47f6595c1201] ==Workflow of Automated Packing Already-Picked Items== The automated processing of packing items that have been picked involves the actions shown in the following diagram.[anchor|#_ee52c6b5-a477-47f1-8d73-66c47468551f][anchor|#_76d736dc-cd0c-4728-9e0b-6767ee1bd0e8][image:UserGuide/Images/WMS_PackwPick.png|popup|450px] To process the packing of items (and use Pack mode) after picking them, you perform the following steps:[anchor|#_7bef02b8-d7c5-4ee8-998c-3cd6748f2317] #''Switch to Pack mode''. #:You switch to Pack mode by scanning or entering the ''@pack'' barcode. The system opens the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_20|Pick, Pack, and Ship] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302020|SO302020]) form with the '''Pack''' tab displayed. #''Scan the document number''. #:To start automated processing, you scan the reference number of shipment to be processed. (If you have switched to Pack mode from Pick mode with the document selected, the document is selected automatically.) The system shows the lines of the scanned document in the table and inserts the reference number of the document that is currently selected for processing in the '''Shipment Nbr.''' box. #''Scan the barcode of the box''. #:You scan the barcode of the box into which the items will be packed. #:((({S:Hint}If the ''Automatic Packaging'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, this step is performed automatically. ))) #''Scan the item barcode''. #:When you scan the barcode of the packed item, the system searches for the item in the lines of the document that is currently selected. If the barcode of the scanned item is specified for a non-base unit of measure, the system converts this quantity to the packed quantity in the base unit of measure for this item; the system also shows the packed quantity in the '''Packed Qty.''' column, and highlights the line (with bold if the line has been processed partially, or in green if the line has been processed in full). #Optional: ''Scan the lot or serial number of the item''. #:This step is required if the item is lot- or serial-tracked, and only if the '''Default Auto-Generated Lot/Serial Nbr.''' check box is cleared on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_10_10_00|Sales Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SO101000|SO101000]) form. If the check box is selected, the system specifies the lot or serial number for the serialized item automatically. #Optional: ''Scan the item quantity''. #:To change the packed quantity in the line that is currently being processed, you switch to Quantity Editing mode by scanning or entering the <tt>&#42;qty</tt> barcode, and manually enter the quantity in the UOM of the scanned item barcode. #''Pack another line''. #:If another item needs to be packed in the current box, you return to scanning the item barcode (return to Step 4), and repeat the process for the item. #''Confirm the box''. #:If all items have been packed in the box, you confirm the current box by scanning the <tt>&#42;ok</tt> barcode or by clicking the '''OK''' button. #:((({S:Hint}This step is performed automatically for the shipments that are being packed to a single box that the system has suggested automatically. ))) #''Enter the box weight''. #:You enter the total weight of the box. #:((({S:Hint}This step is performed automatically for the shipments that are being packed to a single box that the system has suggested automatically. ))) #''Pack another box''. #:If more items need to be packed for the current shipment, you return to scanning the barcode of the box barcode (return to Step 3), and repeat the process for another box. #''Complete the packing process''. #:If you have finished the packing operation and specifying shipping options is not needed, you scan the <tt>&#42;confirm&#42;shipment</tt> barcode or click the '''Confirm Shipment''' button on the form toolbar. The system confirms the shipment that is currently being processed. #:If you have finished the packing operation and want to specify shipping options, you scan the <tt>@ship</tt> barcode to switch to Ship mode (see [[#_6419ca4e-632c-419d-aa23-d600eff07fa6|Workflow of Automated Shipping]).
==Workflow of Automated Packing Without Picking== The automated processing of directly packing items (without first picking them) involves the actions shown in the following diagram.[anchor|#_11398c96-3c05-4f35-b204-60fb5d4775ae][anchor|#_b4d8d5b0-6877-4d4f-b219-92cfb7014a21][image:UserGuide/Images/WMS_PackwoPick.png|popup|450px] To process the packing of items (and use Pack mode) without picking them, you perform the following steps: [anchor|#_540f2ba7-75be-494c-a788-24cf820a187f] #''Switch to Pack mode''. #:You switch to Pack mode by scanning or entering the ''@pack'' barcode. The system opens the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_20|Pick, Pack, and Ship] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302020|SO302020]) form with the '''Pack''' tab displayed. #''Scan the document number''. #:To start automated processing, you scan the reference number of the shipment to be processed. The system shows the lines of the scanned document in the table and inserts the reference number of the document that is currently selected for processing in the '''Shipment Nbr.''' box. #''Scan the barcode of the box''. #:You scan the barcode of the box to which the items will be packed. #:((({S:Hint}If the ''Automatic Packaging'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, this step is performed automatically. ))) #''Scan the location barcode''. #:When you scan the barcode of the location from which the item is being taken for packing, the system searches for the location in the lines of the document that is currently selected. #''Scan the item barcode''. #:When you scan the item barcode of the packed item, the system searches for the item in the lines of the document that is currently selected. If the scanned item barcode corresponds to a non-base unit of measure, the system converts this quantity to the packed quantity in the base unit of measure for this item; the system also displays the packed quantity in the '''Packed Qty.''' column, and highlights the line (with bold if the line is processed partially, or in green if the line is processed in full). #Optional: ''Scan the lot or serial number of the item''. #:This step is required only if the item is lot- or serial-tracked. You need to scan the lot or serial number of the packed item if the '''Default Auto-Generated Lot/Serial Nbr.''' check box is cleared on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_10_10_00|Sales Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SO101000|SO101000]) form. If the check box is selected, the system specifies the lot or serial number for the serialized item automatically. #Optional: ''Scan the item quantity''. #:To change the packed quantity in the line that is currently being processed, you switch to Quantity Editing mode by scanning or entering the <tt>&#42;qty</tt> barcode, and manually enter the quantity in the UOM of the scanned item barcode. #''Pack another line''. #:If another item needs to be packed in the current box, you return to scanning the item barcode (that is, return to Step 4), and repeat the process for the item. #''Confirm the box''. #:If all items are packed in the box, you confirm the current box by scanning the <tt>&#42;ok</tt> barcode or by clicking the '''OK''' button. #:((({S:Hint}This step is performed automatically for the shipments that are being packed to a single box that the system has suggested automatically. ))) #''Enter the box weight''. #:You enter the total weight of the box. #:((({S:Hint}This step is performed automatically for the shipments that are being packed to a single box that the system has suggested automatically. ))) #''Pack another box''. #:If at least one other item needs to be packed for the current shipment, you return to scanning the barcode of the box (that is, return to Step 3), and repeat the process for another box. #''Complete the packing process''. #:If you have finished the packing operation and you don&rsquo;t need to specify shipping options, you scan the <tt>&#42;confirm&#42;shipment</tt> barcode or click the '''Confirm Shipment''' button on the form toolbar. The system confirms the shipment that is currently being processed. #:If you have finished the packing operation, to select shipping options, you scan the <tt>@ship</tt> barcode to switch to Ship mode (see the following section). [anchor|#_6419ca4e-632c-419d-aa23-d600eff07fa6] ==Workflow of Automated Shipping== After you have picked and packed items, you perform the final shipping workflow. In this workflow, you specify shipping options and confirm the shipment, as shown in the following diagram.[anchor|#_8ce84116-ebf0-4fcd-8a14-7af90bac11d3][anchor|#_8088ada2-3a1d-454b-9472-b082e2c4f452][image:UserGuide/Images/WMS_Ship.png|popup|450px] To specify shipping options for the shipment that is currently being processed, you perform the following steps:[anchor|#_74de1687-1474-4a62-bbbc-e3588228ab42] #''Switch to Ship mode''. #:You switch to Ship mode by scanning or entering the ''@ship'' barcode. The system opens the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_20|Pick, Pack, and Ship] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302020|SO302020]) form with the '''Ship''' tab displayed. #''Scan the document number''. #:To start automated processing, you scan the reference number of the shipment to be processed. The system inserts the reference number of the document that is currently selected for processing in the '''Shipment Nbr.''' box. (If you have switched to Ship mode from Pick mode or Pack mode with a document selected, the document is selected automatically.) #:The boxes for the shipment are shown in the '''Packages''' table. #''Select the carrier rate''. #:In the '''Carrier Rates''' table, you select the unlabeled check box in the line of the carrier rate to be used for shipping. #Optional: ''Generate return labels''. #:On the table toolbar of the '''Carrier Rates''' table, click '''Get Return Labels''' to generate return labels for the shipment. #''Confirm the shipment''. #:To confirm the processed shipment, you scan the <tt>&#42;confirm&#42;shipment</tt> barcode, or click the '''Confirm Shipment''' button on the form toolbar.
